description: Roger Federer won the inaugural Laver Cup, beating back a fierce challenge from players from the rest of the world to claim the trophy in a dramatic final match.

title: Rohan Bopanna may pull out of Asian Games
description: Somdev Devvarman pulled out of the Asian Games as he was also unhappy with his run of form in 2014.

title: CoCo Vandeweghe wobbles but roars back to win Elite Trophy opener
description: After dropping her serve twice in the opening set, Vandeweghe rediscovered her rhythm and fired five of her six aces over the course of the next two sets.

title: Leander Paes looked good but team not yet finalised: Mahesh Bhupathi
description: Mahesh Bhupati suggested have helped youngsters like Sriram Balaji and Prajnesh Gunneswaran to score lots of points.

title: Bengaluru Open: Sumit Nagal, Prajnesh  Gunneswaran among four Indians in quarters
description: In another match, Myneni beat Egyptian qualifier Youssef Hossam 6-1, 3-6, 6-1. Hossam Tuesday had knocked out top seed Radu Albot in three sets.

title: Roger Federer suffers shock loss to wildcard Thanasi Kokkinakis at Miami Open
description: Roger Federer suffered a shock 3-6 6-3 7-6(4) defeat to Australian wildcard Thanasi Kokkinakis on Saturday that will cost the Swiss his world number one ranking.

title: Serena Williams’ coach makes plea for honest and open on-court coaching
description: Patrick Mouratoglou admitted gesturing to Serena Williams from the stands during her match with Japan's Naomi Osaka.

title: Petra Kvitova knocks out Caroline Wozniacki to set up Qatar Open final with Garbine Muguruza
description: Petra Kvitova made a shaky start but found her attacking verve midway through the match to beat world number one Caroline Wozniacki 3-6 7-6(3) 7-5 in the Qatar Open.

title: Petra Kvitova beats Garbine Muguruza in Qatar for second straight title
description: Petra Kvitova continued her remarkable comeback by beating Garbine Muguruza in the Qatar Open final on Sunday for her 13th straight win and second consecutive title.

title: US Open Draw: Serena Williams to clash with Maria Sharapova in first round
description: While, Wimbledon finalists Novak Djokovic and Roger Federer are on a semi-final collision course at the US Open after they were placed in the same half of the draw, Rafael Nadal will face John Millman.

title: Wimbledon: Rafael Nadal, Novak Djokovic, Serena Williams ease through; Coco Gauff’s dream run halted
description: 15-year-old American Coco Gauff, whose stunning run at the Wimbledon has made her the talk of the town, lost to former No. 1 Simona Halep 6-3, 6-3 in the fourth round.

title: Wimbledon 2017: Marin Cilic crushes Roberto Bautista Agut to reach quarter-finals
description: Marin Cilic demolished Roberto Bautista Agut 6-2 6-2 6-2 at Wimbledon, doing the damage on distant Court 12 with his pounding serve and thumping forehand. He will meet Gilles Muller in the last eight.

title: Milos Raonic has 17 aces as he reaches Paris Masters 3rd round
description: Big-serving Milos Raonic has been hampered by a recent right ankle injury that forced him to withdraw ahead of the Chinese Open.

title: India Davis Cup team to train in New York ahead of Canada tie
description: Explaining the motive behind the camp in New York, and not Edmonton, Mahesh Bhupathi said, "Courts will not be ready till Sunday (September 10) before tie."

title: French Open 2020: Iga Swiatek powers past Martina Trevisan into semis
description: Iga Swiatek, 19, who thrashed top seed Simona Halep on Sunday to reach her first Grand Slam quarter-final, outclassed qualifier Martina Trevisan 6-3, 6-1 on Tuesday.

title: Dalila Jakupovic retires from Australian Open qualifying after coughing fit
description: Slovenia's Dalila Jakupovic was leading Stefanie Vogele at Melbourne Park when she slumped to her knees at the back of the blue hardcourt suffering breathing difficulties because of the bushfire smoke.

title: Roger Federer beats Stefanos Tsitsipas to send Switzerland into Hopman Cup final
description: Greece, who needed a 3-0 win to progress at the expense of Switzerland, finished with a 2-1 consolation victory. The Swiss topped Group B having already beaten Britain (3-0) and the United States (2-1).

title: Wimbledon 2017: Garbine Muguruza dumps Svetlana Kuznetsova to advance to semi-final
description: Garbine Muguruza advanced confidently into the Wimbledon semi-finals with a calmly efficient and well-controlled 6-3 6-4 victory over Russian seventh seed Svetlana Kuznetsova on Tuesday.

title: Serena Williams passes Maria Sharapova as highest paid sportswoman
description: Maris Sharapova, with $21.9 million, is second to world no.1 Serena Williams - $28.9 million.

title: Angelique Kerber, Garbine Muguruza confirmed for Brisbane International
description: Angelique Kerber, a runner-up in Brisbane last year, will be appearing at the Brisbane Open for the fifth time.

title: Australian Open champion Angelique Kerber hands Sloane Stephens a walkover in Charleston
description: Seventh seed Stephens had dominated the match played in blustery conditions on the green clay in Charleston, leading 6-1 3-0.

title: Australian Open: Coach Magnus Norman the final piece in Stan Wawrinka’s puzzle
description: Stan Wawrinka believed bringing Magnus Norman on board as coach has helped transform him from underachiever to grand slam champion.

title: Caroline Wozniacki, Sam Stosur reach 2nd round at Prague Open
description: Caroline Wozniacki advanced to the second round of the Prague Open by beating Misaki Doi of Japan 6-0, 7-5.

title: Andy Murray says Wimbledon pressure helps him focus better
description: Andy Murray has struggled for consistency this year failing to win any of his five clay events but a third Wimbledon title puts him in a group that includes Briton Fred Perry, world number four Novak Djokovic and German great Boris Becker.

title: Will work hard to restore my confidence, says Novak Djokovic
description: Novak Djokovic's slump began after he won his maiden French Open title in June 2016 to complete a career slam and amass 12 major honours.

title: Australian Open: Leander Paes off to winning start, Sania Mirza loses in women’s doubles
description: Leander Paes and Martina Hingis won their first match against Destanee Aiava and Marc Polmans 6-4 6-3 to progress to the round of 16.

title: Indian Wells: No Roger Federer vs Nick Kyrgios, Aussie withdraws with illness
description: Nick Kyrgios' withdrawal spoiled the highly anticipated match with Roger Federer.

title: Italian Daniele Bracciali banned for life, Potito Starace for 10 years
description: Daniele Bracciali has been banned from tennis for life after being found guilty of match-fixing, the Tennis Integrity Unit (TIU) said on Wednesday.

title: Year after Slam bid at US Open, Serena Williams eyes No. 23, No. 1
description: Serena Williams is at the stage of her career where history is in the offing nearly every time a racket is in her right hand.

title: Ankita Raina will play against Russia’s Veronika Kudermetova in first-round of Mumbai Open
description: Ankita Raina has five singles and seven doubles titles to her credit on the ITF tour.

title: Australian Open 2019: Barbora Krejcikova, Rajeev Ram win mixed doubles title
description: After edging a tight opening set, the experienced Ram and Krejcikova broke early in the second set and held firm to clinch the contest and deny their unseeded rivals.

title: US Open 2017: Madison Keys gives American women half the quarterfinal spots
description: The 15th-seeded Madison Keys joins No. 9 Venus Williams, No. 20 CoCo Vandeweghe and unseeded Sloane Stephens in the final eight at Flushing Meadows. This is the first time US Open has four American women in quarters in 15 years.

title: Australian Open: Kei Nishikori enjoys low profile in Florida, food in Japan
description: Kei Nishikori has been based in the southern U.S for years, honing his game in the sun at the start of each season.

title: Novak Djokovic registers 700th career win to enter Dubai Championships quarters
description: Novak Djokovic is one of three active players to reach 700 wins, the others being Roger Federer with 1067, and Rafael Nadal on 775.

title: Britain’s new number one Kyle Edmund wants ‘legitimate’ Andy Murray battle
description: Kyle Edmund is Britain's top ranked tennis player but says he would have preferred to have beaten Andy Murray fair and square for the honour.

title: Rafael Nadal’s coach unhappy with selection of female Davis Cup captain
description: Gala Leon became the first woman to be appointed captain of the country's Davis Cup team on Sunday,

title: Sloane Stephens beats Elena Vesnina to win title at Charleston

title: Simona Halep into China Open final; becomes new World No 1

description: Zverev overcame a slow start on Thursday to wear down Borna Coric 6-4 6-4 and set up a Miami Open semi-final against Pablo Carreno Busta, who earlier defeated Kevin Anderson.

title: Petra Kvitova could return to tennis in about six months
description: Petra Kvitova underwent nearly four hours of surgery at a specialised clinic in the northern town of Vysoke nad Jizerou.

title: US Open 2020 Round 2, Sumit Nagal vs Dominic Thiem Highlights: Thiem wins in three sets
description: US Open Tennis 2020 Round 2, Sumit Nagal vs Dominic Thiem Highlights: World Number 3 Dominic Thiem beat Sumit Nagal 6-3, 6-3, 6-2.

title: Nick Kyrgios faces investigation after accusing ATP of being ‘corrupt’
description: Nick Kyrgios was fined for unsportsmanlike conduct, verbal abuse, and audible obscenity after arguing with the chair umpire and smashing two rackets during a meltdown.

title: Caroline Wozniacki wobbles on way to China Open round two
description: Caroline Wozniacki had a fright against Wang Qiang in the China Open first round before she composed herself to go through 6-1, 6-7 (4/7), 6-1.

title: What has been your vision for tennis in last 30 years? Somdev Devvarman asks AITA
description: Asked to spell the issues on which he and AITA differed, Somdev said one of the issues was support for players.

title: Australian Open: Sofia Kenin downs Garbine Muguruza to win her first Grand Slam
description: American Sofia Kenin counter-punched her way back from a set down against Garbine Muguruza to win her first Grand Slam title at the Australian Open with a 4-6 6-2 6-2 win on Saturday.

description: World number one Rafael Nadal was also in a punishing mood and kept his preparations for this month's Australian Open on track by dismantling Pablo Cuevas 6-2 6-1 to seal the tie for Spain.

description: Leander Paes is finding it "tough to set new goals" but still spent his off-season getting stronger to remain relevant in modern day tennis.

description: Boris Becker believes Roger Federer's decision to skip the French Open makes him a strong favourite to lift the trophy a few weeks from now on the grass of Wimbledon. The Swiss player had earlier announced his withdrawal from the May 28-June 11 claycourt major.

description: Roger Federer has not played a competitive match since losing to Novak Djokovic in the Australian Open semi-final, since when the COVID-19 pandemic and surgery has sidelined him.

title: Alexander Zverev dominates Auger-Aliassime to win indoor title in Cologne

description: Sachin Tendulkar, who is a close friend of former World No. 1 Roger Federer, has been attending Federer's matches at the Wimbledon earlier as well.

title: 2016 Wimbledon finalist Milos Raonic pulls out of US Open
description: The 11th-ranked Canadian, the runner-up at Wimbledon last year, announced his withdrawal from this season's last Grand Slam tournament on Instagram on Wednesday night.

title: CAS to rule on Maria Sharapova’s doping ban on Tuesday

title: In 2018, Roger Federer turns 20
description: Roger Federer fought off a fierce challenge from Marin Cilic to win the Australian Open in Melbourne for a sixth time. In doing so, he took his majors tally to 20.

title: Serena Williams back doing what she does best at Wimbledon
description: Serena Williams overcame gusting winds and a tumble on Court One's manicured lawn to outclass tricky opponent Arantxa Rus 7-5 6-3 in the first round.

title: Grigor Dimitrov suffers racket-smashing meltdown in Istanbul final

description: Serena Williams returned to the world's top 30 in the WTA rankings released on Monday after finishing as Wimbledon runner-up.

title: Chennai Open: Marin Cilic crashes out to qualifier Josef Kovalik
description: Marin Cilic's campaign came to an end after his was defeated by 117th-ranked Jozef Kovalik 7-6 (5), 5-7, 7-5 in the second round.

title: French Open hikes prize money by 14 percent
description: The overall prize given to players will be lifted by 14 percent  while the winners of the men's and women's singles will get 2 million euros each.

title: US Open 2017: All American women’s semis kick off on sunny day
description: Four American women will play in the semi-finals at the U.S. Open for the first time since 1981, ensuring an American champion will be crowned. Venus Williams, Sloane Stephens, CoCo Vandeweghe and Madison Keys will be in contention for the spot in finals

description: Roger Federer and Serena Williams, both winners of 17 Slams, lift Cincinnati Masters a week before US Open

title: Rafael Nadal aims to carry Olympic boost into US Open
description: Rafael Nadal hopes his Rio Olympics elation carries over to the US Open, which he won in 2010 and 2013.

description: Yuki Bhambri, who had beaten Gael Monfils on Wednesday, moved into the quarter-finals of Citi Open after he beat defeated Guido Pella of Argentina 6-7 6-3 6-1 on Thursday. He will now face Kevin Anderson of South Africa in the next round.

description: The final will feature Pablo Cuevas for a third successive year, with Albert Ramos-Vinolas the Uruguayan's opponent.

description: Vandeweghe was drawn to face Aliaksandra Sasnovich in the first singles match. U.S. Open champion Sloane Stephens will then play Aryna Sabalenka.

title: Hip holds as Nick Kyrgios rolls on at Rogers Cup
description: The 16th seed showed no signs of distress in dispatching Troicki after 51 minutes on a sun-kissed centre court. "I'm feeling it all the time," said Kyrgios. "It's not something that is just going to heal. I can compete so that's the most I can do at the moment."

title: Quashing concerns, sharp Roger Federer wins at Italian Open
description: Novak Djokovic, Andy Murray and seven-time Rome champion Rafael Nadal also advanced in straight sets on the red clay courts at the Foro Italico.

title: Australian, Romanian tennis players banned over betting
description: Neither player sanctioned bets on their own games.

title: Nick Kyrgios enjoys ‘redemption’ for Shanghai meltdown
description: Nick Kyrgios said he wanted to make up for his notorious meltdown last year in Shanghai as he beat Mischa Zverev in the second round of the China Open on Wednesday.

title: Yannick Noah taking no chances ahead of Davis Cup final

title: Prajnesh Gunneswaran, Ankita Raina achieve career-best ranking
description: Prajnesh Gunneswaran, who played his maiden Grand Slam main draw in Australia, and Singapore ITF title winner Ankita Raina on Monday achieved their career-best ranking.

description: Naomi Osaka was adamant that her shock split with coach Sascha Bajin had nothing to do with money but it was because she was determined that her career would not be about putting "success over happiness".

description: Indian Wells Final: Juan Martin Del Potro beat Roger Federer 6-4, 6-7, 7-6 in a two hour and 42 minute marathon to win his first ATP Masters 1000 and Indian Wells title.

title: Wimbledon 2017: Novak Djokovic clash with Adrian Mannarino postponed until Tuesday
description: Novak Djokovic's fourth round match against France's Adrian Mannarino was postponed until Tuesday after the marathon battle between Rafa Nadal and Gilles Muller concluded late on Monday. Organisers said that safety concerns meant they could not move the match to Centre Court.

title: Andy Murray beats Grigor Dimitrov to win China Open
description: The finals victory was Andy Murray's first in three attempts at the China Open.

title: US Open Draw: Serena Williams, Venus Williams could meet in third round

title: In rare event, Sania Mirza-Mahesh Bhupati to play against Leander Paes

description: Playing in her first tournament with new coach Thierry Van Cleemput, Halep raced to a 4-0 lead in the opening set before her ninth-seeded opponent fought back to force a tiebreak.

title: Sparkling Alexander Zverev tastes first victory over Rafael Nadal
description: The Spaniard, who took his major haul to 19 this year, has a patchy record at the tournament. He has never won the title, appeared only eight times despite qualifying on 15 occasions and on his last visit, in 2017, withdrew injured.

title: WTA Finals: Venus Williams rallies past Caroline Garcia to set up Caroline Wozniacki final
description: Venus Williams rallied from the disappointment of losing a tight first set to blast her way past Caroline Garcia 6-7(3) 6-2 6-3 and set up a WTA Finals title showdown against Caroline Wozniacki

title: Simona Halep feels Grand Slam triumph justifies number one ranking
description: World No. 1 Simona Halep also earmarked US Open champion Naomi Osaka as a huge prospect for the future after the Japanese player made her major breakthrough in New York.

title: A win for American Tennis at US Open 2017
description: Slaone Stephens, Madison Keys, CoCo Vandeweghe and Venus Williams became the first US women to sweep all semi-final spots at a grand slam since Wimbledon in 1985.

title: Leander Paes, Rohan Bopanna didn’t practice or play together prior to Rio Olympics, says Mahesh Bhupathi
description: Rohan Bopanna had reluctantly accepted the decision made by AITA to pair him with 42-year-old Leander Paes for Rio Olympics.

title: No Williams-Williams rematch at US Open 2016: Venus Williams out in fourth round
description: Venus Williams failed to convert a match point and lost 4-6, 6-4, 7-6 (3) to 10th-seeded Karolina Pliskova in the fourth round.

title: Did you know? A British Royal family member played at Wimbledon in 1926
description: King George VI, father of Queen Elizabeth was the first ever member of the British Royal Family to participate at the Championships. The King had paired up with Wing Commander Louis Grieg, the then Duke of York.

title: David Ferrer, Garbine Muguruza break Australian hearts in Brisbane
description: David Ferrer, Garbine Muguruza beat local favourites Bernard Tomic and Garbine Muguruza in their respective contests.

description: Andre Agassi, who won eight grand slam titles himself, retired in 2006. The former world number one is in Paris where Novak Djokovic is defending his title, but will leave on holidays with his family next week. Agassi would not have come back to tennis if it weren't for Djokovic.

title: Wimbledon 2018 Day 7 Highlights: Roger Federer, Rafael Nadal, Serena Williams, Novak Djokovic through, all women’s top 10 seeds out
description: Karolina Pliskova was the last of the top 10 seeds to get knocked out of the draw on Day 7 while Serena Williams, Roger Federer, Rafael Nadal and Novak Djokovic all made their way to the quarter-finals.

title: Spinal discord: Focus returns to state of Roger Federer’s injured back
description: Problems within team put aside, focus returns to state of Federer’s injured back before final.

title: Chasing pack closing on Serena Williams, says Martina Navratilova
description: Martina Navratilova said that Serena Williams was under pressure after last year's scintillating run, when she won three Grand Slams.

title: Roger Federer smokes two-handed backhand during practice; watch video
description: Roger Federer is known for his effortless backhands which are not only effective but also put opposite numbers on the backfoot. But he showed at Indian Wells that his double-handed backhand can be equally formidable.

title: US Open 2016: Serena Williams storms into quarter-finals in record-smashing style
description: Serena Williams eased past Kazakhstan's Yaroslava Shvedova 6-2 6-3 to claim her record 308th grand slam match win.

title: Teenager Aryaan Bhatia becomes first Indian tennis player to flunk dope test
description: Aryaan Bhatia became the first Indian tennis player to fail a dope test and has been put under provisional suspension, the National Anti-Doping Agency said on Friday.

title: Sania Mirza wins in WTA Tour return after more than two years
description: Returning to the court after two years, Sania Mirza and Ukrainian partner Nadia Kichenok prevailed 2-6, 7-6 (3), 10-3 over Oksana Kalashnikova of Georgia and Japan's Miyu Kato in a contest lasting one hour and 41 minutes.

title: Confident Kei Nishikori has good feeling about another US Open run
description: Kei Nishikori is brimming with confidence heading into the U.S. Open despite acknowledging the presence of a flock of title contenders.

title: Grigor Dimitrov through to semis in Stockholm
description: Grigor Dimitrov moved closer to qualifying for the ATP World Tour Finals with a 6-3 6-4 victory over Germany's Mischa Zverev to reach the semi-finals of the Stockholm Open

title: US Open: Serena Williams eyes next step on path to history
description: Serena Williams' troublesome right shoulder has held up well so far but she admits it is a constant battle.

title: Ankita Raina stuns former US Open champion Samantha Stosur
description: The Indian, an Asian Games bronze medallist, shocked the fancied Australian 7-5 2-6 6-5 in a gruelling two hours and fifty minutes battle at the WTA 125K event.

title: Alexander Zverev defeats wasteful Marin Cilic again in ATP Finals opener
description: Alexander Zverev produced the slightly steadier tennis in an error-strewn contest to extend his record against Marin Cilic at the O2 Arena to 2-0.

title: Before US Open, Serena Williams warms up with Stanford Classic win
description: Serena's return to fitness has come at just the right time with the US Open set to start on Aug 25.

title: Angelique Kerber and Sloane Stephens headline WTA Elite Trophy field
description: A year after finishing the season as the No. 1-ranked player in the world, Angelique Kerber will be playing at the WTA Elite Trophy with an eye on 2018.

title: US Open 2018: Weary Nick Kyrgios puts heat on officials after first round win
description: Despite playing his opener in the evening after the worst of the ferocious heat had subsided, Nick Kyrgios said conditions remained brutal inside the Louis Armstrong Stadium.

title: Leander Paes to miss Davis Cup tie against Serbia
description: Paes is fighting for the custody of his daughter; the hearing of the case is scheduled around the Serbia tie.

title: ATP must look beyond the ‘big four’, says Jamie Murray
description: Jamie Murray believes ATP must focus on the long-term future of the game and not just promote the 'big four' of men's tennis that include his brother Andy. Jamie said the constant focus on the top players was undermining the quality of tennis

description: Karman Kaur Thandi beat Pei-Chi Lee 7-6, 6-3 and Ankita Raina overcame Chieh-Yu Hsu 6-4, 5-7, 6-1 in India's longest Fed Cup rubber, a two-hour fifty-three-minute encounter.

title: Venus Williams survives marathon battle against Kiki Bertens in Miami
description: Venus Williams' survival to fight another day came as the women's draw remained wide open after the earlier ousting of her sister Serena along with top seed Simona Halep and last week's Indian Wells winner Naomi Osaka.

title: Serena Williams’ US Open begins with tough matchup vs Ekaterina Makarova
description: Serena Williams has played just three singles matches since Wimbledon, hindered by a right shoulder injury.

title: Tomic ‘the Tank Engine’ starts to fire on all cyclinders
description: “It was a lot of emotions throughout the tournament, especially the last match and last point,“ Tomic said

title: US Open 2015 champ Flavia Pennetta to appear in CTL
description: Flavia Pennetta was picked by Mumbai Tennis Masters for the second edition of the Vijay Amritraj-run event.

title: Champions Tennis League 2015: Punjab Marshalls win second match at home ground
description: Elina Svitolina showed why she is rated as one of the talented players in the league.

title: IPTL: Rotation in mind, Indian Aces eyeing a move out of Delhi
description: However, lack of adequate infrastructure including a high capacity stadium to replace the IGI Stadium, remains a concern.

title: Davis Cup: Yuki Bhambri to commence India’s campaign
description: The second singles match will be played between India's Somdev Devvarman and Filip Krajinovic.

title: Australian Open: An ugly win is still a win, says Stan Wawrinka
description: Stan Wawrinka secured his place in the fourth round with a 3-6 6-2 6-2 7-6(7) victory over Serbian Viktor Troicki.

title: Roger Federer chases 99th title, faces Borna Coric in Halle final
description: Roger Federer reached his 12th final in Halle after beating qualifier Denis Kudla 7-6 (1), 7-5 on Saturday.

title: Roger Federer and Belinda Bencic lead Switzerland to Hopman Cup title
description: Roger Federer and Belinda Bencic won the deciding Fast4 mixed doubles 4-3 (3), 4-2 Saturday over Germany to give Switzerland its third Hopman Cup title.

title: Genie Bouchard pays off Super Bowl bet with date at Brooklyn Nets game

description: Jack Sock was impeccable on serve as he did not face a single break point while converting four of six he got against Marin Cilic.

title: With an eye at Rogers Cup final, Sania Mirza celebrates Independence Day
description: Sania Mirza is busy playing Rogers Cup in Toronto where she has already reached the semi-finals.

title: WATCH: Nick Kyrgios practices with fan on Twitter request
description: A fan called Matt Morin contacted Nick Kyrgios on Twitter saying, "@NickKyrgios I'm at rogers cup on tuesday, I know this is a long shot but could we hit for 5 minutes if you're practicing? That'd be dope!"

title: Australian Open: Novak Djokovic dominates Roger Federer, reaches final
description: Novak Djokovic puts up a flawless show in first two sets; later fends off Roger Federer fightback to reach Australian Open final.

title: Top-seeded Dominic Thiem reaches Argentina Open semifinals
description: The sixth-ranked Thiem, the only seeded player left in the clay-court tournament, will face France's Gael Monfils on Saturday.

title: Serena Williams says treatment by USADA ‘shocking’
description: Serena Williams described her treatment by the U.S. Anti-Doping Agency (USADA) as shocking on Sunday as she reacted to news that she had not been home for an out-of-competition test.

title: Britain’s tennis player Dan Evans tests positive for cocaine
description: Dan Evans, who reached his first ATP final this year in Sydney and has played for Britain in the Davis Cup, released a statement saying that he has failed a drugs test in April after taking cocaine.

title: Roger Federer vs Rafael Nadal:  Top 10 matches between the two
description: The rivalry between Roger Federer and Rafael Nadal is widely regarded as the greatest of all time in the history of tennis in the open era.

title: Sumit Nagal one win away from Hamburg Open main draw
description: Nagal, who is on the cusp of breaking into top-200 for the first time in his career, beat the world number 138, Sebastian Ofner 7-5 6-2 in his first round of the clay court event.

title: Wimbledon makes change in using Miss or Mrs. on court
description: The titles will still be used for both women and men when it comes to code violations, medical announcements, and player challenges, according to the All England Club.

title: India may lose Pune Challenger in wake of ATP Challenger Tour revamp
description: A country which is already struggling to host enough tennis tournaments for its top men's players could see the Pune Challenger going off the calendar next year due to additional financial burden

title: N Sriram Balaji-Vishnu Vardhan turn to crowd-funding amid Grand Slam hopes
description: The 2017 season has been the most successful one for the doubles pairing of N Sriram Balaji and Vishnu Vardhan on the professional tour.

title: Davis Cup: Serbia, USA in last eight; defending champions Argentina stay alive
description: Serbia face Spain in the next round if the latter are able to beat Croatia setting up a potential Rafa Nadal, Novak Djokovic clash.

title: Victoria Azarenka retires from Madrid Open with back injury
description: Victoria Azarenka tweaked her back during her opening match against Laura Robson and the pain persisted during her second-round win over Alize Cornet.

title: Andy Murray must overcome mental challenge after injury, says Novak Djokovic
description: Andy Murray has been sidelined for almost a year since losing in the quarter-finals at Wimbledon last July and returns to action on Tuesday at Queen's.

title: I’m not sure: Roger Federer fails to explain his Wimbledon 2018 loss to Kevin Anderson
description: Roger Federer found it hard to explain his shock quarter-final loss to South African Kevin Anderson at Wimbledon on Wednesday.

title: Maria Sharapova determined to prove point on Grand Slam return
description: The 30-year-old Russian was given a wildcard into the tournament by the US Tennis Association (USTA), a move critics complained about earlier in the season but another key step in the road back for the five-time Grand Slam winner.

title: Nick Kyrgios wins Brisbane title in Australian Open boost
description: Nick Kyrgios beat Ryan Harrison 6-4 6-2 in the Brisbane International final on Sunday.

title: Roger Federer races into 15th Basel quarterfinal
description: Roger Federer defeated Benoit Paire for the fifth time without a loss, mowing down the challenger in just 57 minutes in front of a sympathetic audience at the St Jakobshalle on Thursday.

title: AITA clarifies that Mirzas indeed sought their intervention
description: Sania Mirza's family approached AITA to pursue WADA hacking issue, which revealed that several athletes were allegedly allowed to take banned substance.

title: Fed Cup experience will help me on Tour, says Ankita Raina
description: Ankita Raina is confident that she will return to the Pro circuit much richer, in terms of experience.

title: Wimbledon 2018 Day 4: Marin Cilic, Stan Wawrinka exit on on Day 4
description: Wimbledon 2018 Day 4 Highlights: Marin Cilic and Stan Wawrinka lost their second round games to exit.

title: Davis Cup: Yuki Bhambri comes out in support of Mahesh Bhupathi
description: Yuki Bhambri believes the singles rubbers are what will decide the outcome of the tie.

title: US Open 2017 Final: Top 5 quotes from Madison Keys, Sloane Stephens’ emotional clash
description: Sloane Stephens and Madison Keys played out a far from memorable US Open final but their post-match embrace at the net, move to sit alongside before the trophy and warm interaction throughout won many hearts.

title: Spain handed tough draw in new Davis Cup Finals
description: Billed as a soccer-style World Cup of tennis, Spain found themselves in a so-called 'group of death' with defending Davis Cup champions Croatia and a potent Russia side in Group B.

title: Wimbledon 2017: Roger Federer, Andy Murray coast into quarterfinals
description: Roger Federer kept the clean sheet of head-to-head record against 'Baby Fed' Grigor Dimitrov after beating the Bulgarian in straight sets at Wimbledon. He is joined by Andy Murray who faced tough resistance from Benoit Paire.

title: Wimbledon 2017: From Roger Federer and Rafael Nadal to Venus Williams, what to watch
description: Wasn't all that long ago that folks were figuring Roger Federer's best days were long behind him. With defending champion Andy Murray off-form this season, Federer is a popular pick to win Wimbledon for what would be a record eighth time.

title: Novak Djokovic, Rafael Nadal and Marin Cilic head US Open lineup
description: Novak Djokovic didn't have to play in the second when his opponent withdrew with an injury.

title: Wimbledon 2019: Nadal, Djokovic, Federer ease into quarters as legends show Next Gen the way
description: Four-time champion Novak Djokovic advanced along with two-time winner Rafael Nadal and Roger Federer into the quarter-finals of Wimbledon 2019.

title: Wimbledon 2019: Ashleigh Barty, Petra Kvitova into the Round of 16
description: French Open champion, Barty made mincemeat of Harriet Dart to progress into the round of 16, wrapping up victory by winning the 20th consecutive set of a remarkable run of dominance.

title: Roger Federer-Novak Djokovic face off at ATP World Tour Finals
description: The two have clashes a number of times in the calendar year as they faced off each other at US Open and Wimbledon.

title: Wimbledon 2016, Day 4: Andy Murray, Eugenie Bouchard into Rd 3, Garbine Muguruza stunned
description: Top seeds Andy Murray and Agnieszka Radwanska enter Rd 3 with comfortable wins in their Rd 2 contests.

title: Wimbledon 2019: Cori Gauff backs up Venus win to reach third round
description: Cori  Gauff showed her stunning first-round defeat of Venus Williams was no flash in the pan as she outclassed Magdalena Rybarikova 6-3 6-3 to reach the third round of Wimbledon.

title: After Grigor Dimitrov, Borna Coric tests positive for COVID-19
description: Borna Coric, who played in Novak Djokovic's Adria Tour exhibition tournament at the weekend, said on Monday he had tested positive for COVID-19.

title: US Open 2017: Flushing Meadows darling Juan Martin Del Potro thanks crowd for epic win
description: 24th seeded Juan Martin Del Potro, whose career has been plagued by multiple injuries, said he was about to retire when he drew some energy from the crowd as Dominic Thiem was cruising to victory.

title: Simona Halep, Elina Svitolina chase World No 1 ranking; scenarios explained
description: Garbine Muguruza's early exit from China Open in Beijing has opened the door for Simona Halep and Elina Svitolina to take her World No 1 ranking.

title: Roger Federer, defending champ John Isner to meet in Miami Open final
description: Roger Federer dominated a semifinal battle of the ages, beating 19-year-old Canadian Denis Shapovalov 6-2, 6-4. John Isner also bested a Canadian teenager, 18-year-old qualifier Felix Auger-Aliassime, 7-6 (3), 7-6 (4).

title: French Open 2017: Rafael Nadal sets up final against Stan Wawrinka
description: Rafael Nadal reached his 10th French Open after beating Dominic Thiem 6-3 6-4 6-0 in the semi-final and set up a match with 2015 champion Stan Wawrinka who took out world number one Andy Murray in an epic five-setter 6-7 6-3 5-7 7-6 6-1.

title: US Open 2018: Rafael Nadal drops 1st set 6-0 before edging Dominic Thiem in 5-set thriller
description: The defending champion and No. 1 seed Rafel Nadal recovered from his disastrous start and other stumbles along the way to beat No. 9 Dominic Thiem 0-6, 6-4, 7-5, 6-7 (4), 7-6 (5) for a semifinal berth.

title: Wimbledon 2016, Day 6: Novak Djokovic stunned by Sam Querrey; Kvitova crashes out; Cilic, Halep win
description: Defending champion Novak Djokovic was undone by Sam Querre on Saturday.

title: US Open singles champions to earn record $3.7 million
description: The U.S. Tennis Association announced Tuesday that the total purse for the tournament will be $50.4 million, a nearly 9 percent increase from last year. The previous winners of the final Grand Slam tournament Stan Wawrinka and Angelique Kerber earned $3.5 million.

title: Cancer victim gives Nick Kyrgios higher purpose in life
description: Nick Kyrgios has made no bones about not taking tennis seriously enough, and on Monday said it was down to feeling like he had no real purpose in life.

title: Australian Open: Can Dominic Thiem break the Slam barrier or will Novak Djokovic claim his 17th?
description: Dominic Thiem, 26, has never won a Grand Slam title. Novak Djokovic, 32, on the other hand, is aiming to win his 17th Slam title and inch closer to Roger Federer's mark of 20 Slam titles and Rafael Nadal's mark of 19.

title: Wimbledon 2017: Sania Mirza visits injured Bethanie Mattek-Sands in the hospital
description: Sania Mirza and Sorana Cirstea visited an injured Bethanie Mattek-Sands in the hospital after the American suffered an agonising knee injury during her second round match at Wimbledon. She confirmed on Saturday she will need surgery.

title: Wimbledon 2018: Kiki Bertens ends Venus Williams’ days of living dangerously
description: Venus Williams became the latest top-10 seed to perish at Wimbledon after she was beaten 6-2 6-7(5) 8-6 in a pulsating third-round match by Dutchwoman Kiki Bertens.

title: Ramkumar Ramanathan stuns World No. 8 Dominic Thiem at Antalya Open
description: Ramkumar Ramanathan recorded a straight sets win over French Open 2017 semi-finalist Dominic Thiem at the Antalya Open in Turkey. In a match that lasted a minuted under an hour, Ramanathan beat the Austrian 6-3, 6-2.

title: Make American Tennis Great Again, mission accomplished
description: For years the United States Tennis Association (USTA) has been working on a plan to 'Make American Tennis Great Again' and on Wednesday it all came together with American women completing a sweep of the U.S. Open quarter-finals.

title: Tomas Berdych progresses in Stuttgart Open, Jerzy Janowicz beats Grigor Dimitrov
description: Despite 16 aces, Dimitrov failed to convert any of his three break-point chances. Janowicz will next play either Benoit Paire or Peter Gojowczyk. Third-seeded Tomas Berdych also advanced, beating Bernard Tomic 7-6 (4), 6-2.

title: Angelique Kerber ousts local favorite Naomi Osaka at Pan-Pacific Open
description: Angelique Kerber was knocked out of the U.S. Open by the Japanese teenager in straight sets. Kerber will play either Madison Brengle or Daria Kasatkina in the next round.

title: Australian Open: Rafa Nadal, Grigor Dimitrov reach last 16
description: Rafa Nadal and Grigor Dimitrov stormed into the fourth round of the Australian Open.

title: Maharashtra Open 2019: Serve-and-volleying Ivo Karlovic stands test of time
description: Now in the 19th year of his career, Ivo Karlovic tops the leaderboard for most aces by any player in the history of the tour – 13024.

title: Novak Djokovic vs Stan Wawrinka big-game talents in US Open 2016 Final
description: Defending champion Novak Djokovic owns a 19-4 career head-to-head advantage over Stan Wawrinka.

title: Membership in Big Four not of huge interest for Stan Wawrinka
description: With his US Open win over Noavk Djokovic, Stan Wawrinka captured his third major title, matching the haul of long-standing Big Four member Andy Murray.

title: Australian Open: Andreas Seppi ends Roger Federer’s Australian summer
description: Roger Federer was sent packing by Andreas Seppi as Rafael Nadal battled on to progress to the 4th round.

title: Wimbledon 2016: Nick Kyrgios must avoid physical battle against Andy Murray, says Hewitt
description: Nick Kyrgios has been in sparkling form so far, largely letting his racket do the talking, and his match-up against second seed Andy Murray.

title: Novak Djokovic, Rafael Nadal, Andy Murray cruise into Madrid quarters
description: Novak Djokovic is playing in Madrid for the first time in three years, but hasn't taken long to adjust to the different conditions

title: Rafael Nadal moves up to No. 2 in ATP ranking, Novak Djokovic slides to fourth
description: Rafael Nadal moved up by two spots to stand at the highest placing in the ATP rankings since October 2014 - No. 2 while Jelena Ostapenko jumped from 47th to a career-high 12th in the WTA rankings after the two won the French Open title this weekend.

title: Sam Stosur urges Margaret Court to stop comments about same-sex marriage
description: In a letter published in The West Australian newspaper last week, Margaret Court wrote that she would stop flying Qantas where possible because the Australian airline has become an active promoter for same-sex marriage.

title: Australian Open 2018: Jo Wilfried Tsonga survives Denis Shapovalov in five sets
description: The 32-year-old former runner-up, Jo Wilfried Tsonga, was staring at a second successive grand slam defeat to the 18-year-old Denis Shapovalov when he trailed 5-2 in the decider.

title: Fresh arrivals look to warm up London party
description: Djokovic is seeking a 3rd consecutive title alongside the River Thames, one that would seal the world no.1 ranking.

title: Shot clock gets mixed reception on Grand Slam debut
description: US Open moved into day three, players were still grappling with the new shot-clock rules, which allow players 25 seconds after the chair umpire announces the score to make their serve.

title: French Open 2019 Women’s Final: Barty defeats Vondrousova 6-1, 6-3 to win the title
description: French Open 2019 Women's Final Tennis, Ashleigh Barty vs Marketa Vondrousova Tennis: Barty faces Vondrousova in the women's singles final.

title: Stan Wawrinka’s threepeat showing in Chennai
description: Stan Wawrinka defeats teenager Coric 6-3, 7-5 to claim his third consecutive title at India’s ATP 250 event.

title: Roger Federer suggests Wimbledon organisers reconsider all-white playing gear rule
description: Wimbledon's insistence on an all-white playing gear, a rule going back to the 19th century, is strictly observed with only the tiniest amounts of colour allowed.

title: Athletes should be grateful for Colin Kaepernick, says Serena Williams
description: Colin Kaepernick began a wave of protests by NFL players two seasons ago, kneeling during the national anthem to protest police brutality and racial inequality.

title: French Open 2017: Resilient Simona Halep has unfinished business in Paris
description: 'Not finished', Simona Halep quipped when asked to reflect on her French Open campaign after handling Czech Karolina Pliskova's power to reach her second final at Roland Garros. She is never finished. Halep prevailed 6-4 3-6 6-3 to set up a date with Jelena Ostapenko.

title: Wimbledon 2015: Class is permanent, form is temporary
description: Seven-time champion Federer outclasses big-serving Groth but Nadal-slayer Dustin Brown loses to Victor Troicki.

title: US Open 2016: France’s Lucas Pouille, Gael Monfils face off for spot in semi-final
description: Lucas Pouille and Gael Monfils to meet on Tuesday at the US Open with at least one Frenchman guaranteed a spot in the semifinals.

title: Novak Djokovic closes in on eclipsing Federer, but is still never the favourite
description: Novak Djokovic is on course to win three or more Majors and break Federer's all-time record. Why then, despite arguably being the most dominant player since 2008, does Djokovic not draw the kind of adulation that Federer and Nadal do?

title: US Open 2018: Madison Keys books second successive semi-final berth
description: Madison Keys faces Naomi Osaka in the semi-final after a 6-4, 6-3 win over Carla Suarez Navarro in the quarters at the US Open.

title: Australian Open 2019: My idol today became pretty much my rival, says Stefanos Tsitsipas
description: Stefanos Tsitsipas saved all 12 break points he gave up to the Swiss and was clinical in the riveting final tiebreak.

title: Enrique Lopez Perez gets eight-year ban for match fixing
description: Enrique Lopez Perez, who reached a career-high singles ranking of 154 in 2018 and a best doubles ranking of 135 last year, was also fined $25,000.

title: Italian Open: Stan Wawrinka falls, Novak Djokovic into quarter-finals
description: Novak Djokovic saw off Roberto Bautista-Agut 6-4 6-4 on Court Centrale to reach the quarters for an 11th successive year.

title: ATP, WTA eye outside help for online abuse of tennis players
description: Stalking and player safety are real concerns in a sport shaken by the stabbing of International Tennis Hall of Famer Monica Seles during a tournament 25 years ago.

title: Davis Cup singles to remain best-of-five set affairs
description: Davis Cup singles matches will continue to be decided over the best-of-five sets after a proposal to shorten the contests failed to achieve the required mandate, the International Tennis Federation (ITF) said on Friday.

title: Wimbledon 2016: Wily campaigner Tomas Berdych wins Czech showdown
description: Tomas Berdych defeated Jiri Vesely by 4-6 6-3 7-6(8) 6-7(9) 6-3 to seal his place in Wimbledon men's quarter-final.

title: For me Champions Tennis League is all about friendship: Leander Paes
description: The Vijay Amritraj-conceptualised league is kicking off on Monday with a double-header in the Delhi and Hyderabad.

title: Sumit Nagal, Ramkumar Ramanathan confirm availability for Pakistan tie
description: Though Sumit Nagal and Ramkumar Ramanathan will strengthen India's squad, Prajnesh Gunneswaran's unavailability might hit them as he is getting married on the first day of the Davis Cup tie.

title: Roger Federer, Rafael Nadal to clash in Indian Wells semi-final
description: The multiple Grand Slam champions both won their quarter-finals on Friday, although Nadal in particular had to work hard to overcome Russian Karen Khachanov 7-6(2) 7-6(2) in a match during which he required treatment on the knee.

title: US Open 2018: What happened in the Serena Williams, chair umpire Carlos Ramos controversy?
description: US Open women's final between Naomi Osaka and Serena Williams finished in controversial manner with the American involved in verbal clash with chair umpire Carlos Ramos.

title: Wimbledon 2018: Simona Halep blames ‘unprofessional’ performance for exit
description: Simona Halep described her performance as 'unprofessional' after the world number one suffered a shock third-round defeat by Taiwan's Hsieh Su-wei at Wimbledon on Saturday.

title: ATP Finals: Andy Murray beats Stan Wawrinka, faces Milos Raonic in semifinals
description: Andy Murray finishes 3-0 in the group stages of the ATP World Tour finals and keeps the race for World No 1 going.

title: John McEnroe regrets his comments on Serena Williams
description: McEnroe previously said that Serena Williams was the best female player ever but then declined to label her the best player overall, prompting Williams to ask McEnroe for 'respect'.

title: Dominic Thiem OK with how many of Big 3 are in US Open

title: Angelique Kerber reaches Sydney semis, Camila Giorgi ousts Agnieszka Radwanska

title: ITF chief David Haggerty confident of ‘one-event’ solution for Davis Cup
description: This weekend's Davis Cup final between France and Croatia in Lille is the last one in the 118-year-old competition's current home-and-away format with next year's event to culminate in an 18-nation, World Cup-style showdown in Madrid in November.

title: Caroline Wozniacki pulls out of Sydney opener with wrist injury
description: World number eight Caroline Wozniacki pulled out of her first match at the Sydney International with a wrist injury.

title: Serena Williams gives birth to baby girl, confirms coach Patrick Mouratoglou
description: Coach Patrick Mouratoglou confirmed on Twitter that Serena Williams has given birth to a baby girl. The 35-year-old American, who has not competed since winning the Australian Open in January, has posted several videos to social media showing her hitting balls during her pregnancy.

title: Roger Federer pulls out of Madrid Open due to back injury
description: Roger Federer travelled to Madrid for the tournament but was unable to practice and announced his withdrawal on Monday.

title: AITA willing to elect new president after derecognition by Sports Ministry
description: Sports ministry has asked AITA to elect a new president within 90 days after Anil Khanna had refused the role at the AGM.

title: Novak Djokovic’s mental strength, level of tennis difficult to equal: Rafael Nadal
description: Rafael Nadal and Novak Djokovic will play an exhibition match in Bangkok on Friday.

title: French Open 2017: Master of defence Simona Halep downs Karolina Pliskova to reach final
description: Romanian Simona Halep showed the full extent of her defensive skills to beat Karolina Pliskova 6-4 3-6 6-3 and reach her second French Open final. She will become world number one if she defeats Jelena Ostapenko in showdown.

title: Novak Djokovic beats Kevin Anderson to win fourth Wimbledon title
description: Novak Djokovic was back to his brutal best as he beat South African eighth seed Kevin Anderson 6-2 6-2 7-6(3) to win the Wimbledon men's singles title for the fourth time on Sunday.

title: It’s the best preparation I’ve ever had for Wimbledon: Roger Federer
description: Win at Halle and love-affair with Wimbledon grass gives Federer his best and perhaps last chance to win a Grand Slam.

title: Wimbledon 2016: Dominika Cibulkova on a roll, lines up Agnieszka Radwanska next
description: The 19th seed beat 2014 runner-up Eugenie Bouchard 6-4 6-3 on Saturday to reach the last 16 without the loss of a set.

title: Karolina Pliskova beats Caroline Wozniacki to win Doha WTA final
description: Karolina Pliskova beat Caroline Wozniacki for the first time and won their Qatar Open final 6-3, 6-4 on Saturday.

title: Australian Open comeback an ‘outrageous plan’, admits Serena Williams
description: Serena Williams is expected to give birth at the end of the year and add to her already impressive tally of 23 Grand Slam titles. But with a year away from the sport, she knows it will be a difficult ask if she doesn't win outright.

title: Prajnesh Gunneswaran qualifies for his maiden ATP World Tour event
description: Prajnesh Gunneswaran qualified for the singles main draw of an ATP World event for the first time in his career when he defeated Christian Harrison in the final round of the Mercedes Cup Qualifiers in Stuttgart, Germany.

title: Australian Open: ‘Divine’ Novak Djokovic up for another epic against greatest rival Rafa Nadal
description: If Rafa Nadal's Australian Open semi-final win over Greek sensation Stefanos Tsitsipas was one-sided, Novak Djokovic showed he could be even more brutal in his victory against Lucas Pouille.

title: French Open 2017: Andy Murray takes on tricky Karen Khachanov for a spot in last eight
description: Andy Murray will need to keep his guard up when he takes on rising star Karen Khachanov for a spot in the last eight with the Russian having already caused two upsets on his French Open debut. Khachanov eliminated Tomas Berdych in round two.

title: US Open 2017: I’m definitely here to win my matches, not for consolations, says Venus Williams
description: Venus Williams rejected the suggestion she might be content to serve as an inspiration to younger players after her 6-1 0-6 7-5 defeat to fellow American Sloane Stephens in the semi-finals of the US Open on Thursday.

title: Lindsay Davenport thinks Maria Sharapova, Victoria Azarenka could make WTA Finals
description: Victoria Azarenka hadn't played in a tournament since last year's French Open until coming back last month as a mother. Maria Sharapova served a 15-month ban after testing positive for the newly banned drug meldonium at the Australian Open in January 2016.

title: Stefanos Tsitsipas eclipses Roger Federer to reach ATP Finals title match
description: Stefanos Tsitsipas stunned favourite Roger Federer to reach the final on his debut at the ATP Finals on Saturday, beating the six-time champion 6-3 6-4 at the O2 Arena.

title: Young gun Alexander Zverev to meet veteran Philipp Kohlschreiber in Munich final
description: Defending champion Alexander Zverev advanced to the final of the Munich Open after a hard-fought 7-5 6-2 victory over South Korean's Chung Hyeon on Saturday.

title: The game has become a little bit more crazy: Rafael Nadal
description: Against Fernando Verdasco, a player he had beaten 14 times in 16 meetings, Rafael Nadal's game just looked stale.

title: Stan Wawrinka, the man who broke the Big four hegemony
description: Stan Wawrinka's career has been defined by recent highs and some early lows.

title: Australian Open 2019: Petra Kvitova crashes Ashleigh Barty party to reach semi-finals
description: Petra Kvitova trampled on the hopes of the host nation at the Australian Open by thrashing Ashleigh Barty 6-1 6-4 to reach her first Grand Slam semi-finals in five years.

title: Davis Cup champions Croatia among six seeded nations for finals
description: Last year's runners-up France were named top seeds on Monday while Belgium and the United States were also seeded alongside wildcards Britain and Argentina.

title: American men battle to end drought at US Open 2018
description: American men have failed to emulate the glory of their female compatriots at the U.S. Open in recent years and appear to have little hope of ending a 15-year drought.

title: Next couple of years is the last few where I have a chance to compete in the majors, says Andy Murray
description: Before the Wimbledon kicks off, Murray will have another challenge - which is at the Queen's Club (Aegon Championships) next week and Murray will be looking to an impact there. However, what he must also be wary about is to be fit for the Wimbledon.

title: Novak Djokovic kicks off Wimbledon 2017 campaign after dismal year
description: A lot can happen in 12 months. Just ask Novak Djokovic who came into last year's Wimbledon as holder of all four grand slam titles but has since relinquished his grip on the men's game in spectacular fashion. The Serb has not lifted a grand slam trophy since last year's French Open.

title: Jelena Ostapenko first talked of winning French Open at 10, says mother Jelena Jakovleva
description:
Jelena Ostapenko, who will rise to world number 12 from 47 following Saturday's win, also worked a lot on her forehand, which was then her weakest shot.
"Her forehand was so-so. So she worked hard on it." Halep realised just how hard her opponent had worked on that on Saturday.

title: Australian Open 2019: Novak Djokovic dominates Tsonga re-match to reach third round
description: Eleven years after beating Jo-Wilfried Tsonga for the 2008 Australian Open, top seed Novak Djokovic bested the Frenchman again at Melbourne Park to reach the third round.

title: Milos Raonic waits out rain, reaches Delray Beach quarter-finals
description: Milos Raonic has won the last of his eight ATP Tour titles last year in Brisbane, Australia.

title: French Open 2017: Andre Agassi stars as Novak Djokovic romps to second-round win
description: The star appeal of Andre Agassi was undeniable at the French Open on Wednesday as his new charge Novak Djokovic romped to a second-round win with 6-1 6-4 6-3 win over Joao Sousa.

title: Donald Young accuses Ryan Harrison of racial slur during New York Open match
description: Young accused Harrison of commenting on him being a black tennis player in the middle of the match.

title: Australian Open: Roger Federer eases past Marton Fucsovics into quarter-finals
description: Roger Federer is the oldest man to reach the quarter-finals of the Australian Open since Ken Rosewall in 1977. He next faces Tomas Berdych at Melbourne Park.

title: India has enough money for tennis but AITA has no will: Karti Chidambaram
description: Karti said if India does not have quality singles players, it is because they are lost in transition due to lack of support from AITA.

title: French Open 2018: Yuki Bhambri gets Chinese Taipei’s Yen-Hsun Lu in first round
description: Yuki Bhambri will play his first round at the Roland Garros against Chinese Taipei's Yen-Hsun Lu. The second grand slam of the year had its draw made on Thursday evening in Paris.

title: US Open: Despite wind, Serena Williams breezes through
description: 17-time Grand Slam winner struggles with serve but still prevails over Vania King 6-1, 6-0.

title: No room for excuses now: Mahesh Bhupathi ahead of Davis Cup tie vs Italy
description: Mahesh Bhupathi made it clear that India won't miss veteran Leander Paes during their upcoming Davis Cup Qualifier against fancied Italy at Calcutta South Club on Friday-Saturday.

title: ATP warns players of unsolicited help from French firm for creation of solidarity fund
description: "We recommend that you be cautious and confirm the legitimacy of any unsolicited approaches that you receive before you decide to pursue them," said ATP’s letter to players.

title: IPTL 2: Indian Aces register second win on the trot
description: Sania Mirza, Bopanna won it yet again for the Indian Aces by brushing aside Belinda Bencic and Melo 6-3 in the mixed doubles.

title: Julia Goerges rallies to beat Andrea Petkovic in Citi Open semi-final
description: Julia Goerges made it through an all-German semi-final at the Citi Open on Saturday with a 5-7 6-4 7-5 win over Andrea Petkovic, setting up a title match against Ekaterina Makarova.

title: French Open 2019: Novak Djokovic vs Dominic Thiem French semis to resume on Saturday

description: Aryna Sabalenka surged up the WTA rankings last year, winning her first two titles and ending it just outside the top 10 and arrived in Melbourne fresh from winning in Shenzhen.

description: Sumit Nagal's claims of innocence are being challenged by Anand Amritraj, whose captaincy swansong would be the tie against New Zealand.
