description: On match point, Roberto Bautista Agut scurried back from the net to retrieve a lob, hitting a 'tweener' shot between his legs, before running down a drop shot and poking a winner down the line.

title: Agnieszka Radwanska, Andy Murray continue winning run at the Hopman Cup
description: Radwanska and Murray picked up morale-boosting victories on Wednesday to keep their Australian Open preparations on track.

title: Davis Cup: France set up Serbia semi-final after doubles win
description: Julian Benneteau and Nicolas Mahut edged Dominic Inglot and Jamie Murray 7-6 (7), 5-7, 7-5, 7-5.

title: French Open prize money increases by eight percent from 2018
description: French Open prize money will increase by 8 percent at this year's tournament to 42.661 million euros ($48.6 million).

title: France seeking major upset in Fed Cup final against Czech Republic
description: The Czechs have won four of the last five editions while France are in the final for the first time since 2005.

title: Rohan Bopanna-Florin Mergea enter ATP Mercedes Cup final
description: The Indo-Romanian pair will face third seed Brazil's Bruno Soares and Alexander Peya of Austria in the final

title: What Justine Henin misses: One-handed backhand and a dominant star
description: The Belgian Justine Henin was in the capital to attend the fifth edition of Rendezvous a Roland-Garros, a junior wild card event won by Mann Maulik Shah and Humera Shaikh on Wednesday.

title: Australian Open: I’ll be back, says thwarted Andy Murray
description: Andy Murray vowed to return as strong as ever after his bid for a maiden Australian Open title was brought to a stunning end by Mischa Zverev.

title: US Open: Belinda Bencic bounds into first-ever Grand Slam semi-final
description: Belinda Bencic next plays either Canada's Bianca Andreescu or Belgium's Elise Mertens, who face off under the lights at Arthur Ashe Stadium later.

title: Inexperienced US faces weakened Czech Republic in Fed Cup final
description: United States captain Kathy Rinaldi has had a winning formula since taking over the Fed Cup team, and she's not expected to change anything in this year's final against the Czech Republic.

title: Top seed Simona Halep stunned by Hsieh Su-wei in Wimbledon 2018 third round
description: Women's top seed Simona Halep crashed out in the third round of Wimbledon on Saturday when she was beaten 3-6 6-4 7-5 by Taiwan's Hsieh Su-wei.

title: Aus Open 2016: Dominating win takes Sania Mirza-Martina Hingis into women’s doubles final
description: Sania Mirza and Martina Hingis will take on seventh seed pair of Andrea Hlavackova and Lucie Hradecka in the final.

title: When you have injuries, it’s difficult, the comebacks: Rafael Nadal
description: The rangy Czech Berdych played majestically to reach his second semi-final at Melbourne Park.

title: Nick Kyrgios rips Rafael Nadal to reach semifinals, Karolina Pliskova takes two in Cincinnati
description: Karolina Pliskova completed a match that was suspended overnight because of rain, beating qualifier Camila Giorgi in three sets. Whereas, Rafael Nadal was sloppy at the outset and on the defensive for much of a 6-2, 7-5 loss that lasted an hour and 20 minutes.

title: Davis Cup: Steve Darcis scolds himself for being ‘appalling’ in Belgian loss
description: Steve Darcis scolded himself for being "appalling" as Belgium missed out on a maiden title, suffering a 3-2 defeat to hosts France on Sunday

title: Leander Paes-Divij Sharan reaches quarters at Knoxville Challenger
description: Leander Paes and Purav Raja advanced with a 6-2 6-4 win over American team of Kevin King and Bradley Klahn in just 55 minutes.

title: Eastbourne 2018: Defending champion Karolina Pliskova stunned by Aryna Sabalenka
description: Sabalenka's first victory over a top-10 opponent means that in the last eight she will face former champion Agnieszka Radwanska, who got the better of Latvian Jelena Ostapenko.

title: Australian Open: Simona Halep faces tricky test against Kaia Kanepi
description: Simona Halep begins her Australian Open campaign against Kaia Kanepi on Tuesday in a rematch of their US Open meeting which the world number one lost in straights sets.

title: Roger Federer eases through in Cincinnati
description: Roger Federer quickly shook off the rust, needing just an hour and nine minutes to beat Agut.

title: Serena Williams and the rules of engagement
description: Serena Williams is in Melbourne aiming for an Open-era record 23rd Grand Slam title and Alexis Ohanian has been at her matches.

title: ‘Health of players, fans and staff a priority’: Australian Open organisers on bushfire smoke
description: With qualifying for the season's first Grand Slam starting on January 14, Australia Open director Craig Tiley said officials can halt play if smoke poses a danger to players' health.

title: Thor actor Chris Hemsworth happy to lend his hammer to Juan Martin Del Potro for US Open 2017; watch video
description: Chris Hemsworth on Friday wished del Potro for his next match against Rafael Nadal with the message, "Lost my hammer again... but as they say, sharing is caring. Good luck @delpotrojuan. @rogerfederer @usopen #USOpen #THORtro #ThorRagnarok"

title: Wimbledon 2017: Venus Williams’ road to the final
description: In 2011, Venus Williams pulled out of the US Open after being diagnosed with Sjorgen’s Syndrome. The disease causes fatigue and pain in the joints and, with Williams on the wrong side of 30, many would have wondered if we would ever get to see her again in the final stages of a major tournament, […]

title: Defending champion Rafael Nadal withdraws from US Open
description: A wrist injury forced Nadal to skip the tournament; he also missed Rogers Cup and Cincinnati Open.

title: Wimbledon 2018: Garbine Muguruza gets ready to defend her title
description: Garbine Muguruza isn't lacking confidence as she starts the buildup to defending her Wimbledon title.

title: US Open 2015: Novak Djokovic made to work hard for quarters berth
description: Novak Djokovic smashed his racquet after losing the second set but recovered to win the match 6-3 4-6 6-4 6-3.

title: US Open 2017: Three slams in a year sounds surreal to me, says Roger Federer
description: Skipping the Rio de Janeiro Olympics, the U.S. Open and other tournaments last year allowed Roger Federer to return to the ATP Tour refreshed and reinvigorated, not to mention fully fit. And the results have started to come in.

title: Maria Sharapova: Everything you need to know about tennis star
description: Maria Sharapova tells a news conference in Los Angeles that she tested positive at this year's Australian Open for meldonium.

title: STA-AITA Tennis Tourney City boy Aarav Joshi makes his way to semi-final
description: FACING A tough challenge from Shubham Singh, local lad Aarav Joshi made his way to the boys’ U-14 semi-final with a 7-5, 7-5 win.

title: Highly unlikely US Open would be held without fans: USTA head Mike Dowse
description: The U.S. Open, which is scheduled to run from Aug. 31 to Sept. 13, is both the largest and loudest of the four Grand Slam events on the tennis calendar.

title: Rafael Nadal holds off teenage talent Alexander Zverev in five set classic at Australian Open
description: Rafael Nadal beat Alexandor Zverev 4-6 6-3 6-7(5) 6-3 6-2 to advance to the fourth round.

title: Maria Sharapova to make grasscourt return in Birmingham
description: Maria Sharapova will compete at the Birmingham Classic grasscourt event in the lead-up to Wimbledon, Britain's Lawn Tennis Association (LTA) announced on Wednesday.

title: Rafa Nadal pulls out of Rotterdam citing fatigue
description: Tournament director Richard Krajicek says he tried unsuccessfully to get Roger Federer or a top-five ranked player to replace Rafa Nadal.

title: Tennis at the (Bathroom) Breaking Point
description: With matches often stretching past 90 minutes, sometimes a player truly has to answer nature’s call during a set.

title: Eugenie Bouchard beats fallen idol Maria Sharapova in Madrid
description: After Eugenie Bouchard called Maria Sharapova "a cheater" last week, she shocked the Russian 7-5, 2-6, 6-4 in the second round of the Madrid Open.

title: Garbine Muguruza poses formidable final hurdle for resurgent Venus Williams
description: While it was Conchita Martinez who defeated Martina Navratilova in 1994, standing in the way of Venus Williams and a sixth title, an almost unthinkable 17 years after her first, is the tall and powerful Garbine Muguruza.

title: Wimbledon 2016: Nick Kyrgios overcomes gritty Czech veteran Radek Stepanek
description: Australia 15th seed Nick Kyrgios beat Radek Stepanek by 6-4 6-3 6-7(9) 6-1 on court 2.

title: Andy Murray a doubt for Davis Cup with elbow injury
description: Andy Murray is expected to be left out of the Great Britain squad, which will be announced on Tuesday.

title: US Open 2017: Roger Federer ready to roll at Flushing Meadows
description: The next act of Roger Federer's remarkable renaissance starts when the 19-times grand slam champion begins pursuit of a sixth U.S. Open title against American outsider Frances Tiafoe.

title: Ashleigh Barty sets up Beijing final showdown with Naomi Osaka
description: Ashleigh Barty claimed her 19th win in a three-setter this year and her third in a row after beating Zheng Saisai in the last 16, and seventh seed Petra Kvitova in the quarter-finals, with both matches lasting more than two hours.

title: Andy Murray advances to third round in Madrid Open
description: Andy Murray made his debut at the Madrid Open with a comfortable 6-4, 6-3 win over Marius Copil of Romania in the second round.

title: Andrey Rublev turns tables to dump Tomas Berdych out of China Open
description: Andrey Rublev recovered from a set and a break down to storm past former winner Tomas Berdych and into the China Open quarter-finals.

title: Comeback kid? Tommy Haas, 38, returns for proper farewell
description: Tommy Haas has a job as the tournament director at the Indian Wells event when he finally decides to hang up his tennis racket.

title: Davis Cup: ‘Small fish’ Ramkumar Ramanathan needs to swim in big pond
description: Time has come for Ramkumar Ramanathan to start playing more challengers and ATP events to climb the rungs in international tennis.

title: Rohan Bopanna serves home-grown brew at Tata Open
description: At the ATP-250 Tata Open Maharashtra underway at Balewadi, Rohan Bopanna makes it a point to be there at the coffee counter where his own coffee brew is being sold.

title: Billie Jean King wants three-setters for men at Grand Slams
description: Men currently play best-of-five sets at the four major events and the three-set format is used in other ATP World Tour tournaments while women play best-of-three matches in most competitions, including the grand slams.

title: Wimbledon 2017: Don’t blame the courts for players’ tumbles, says All England chief Richard Lewis
description: World number one Andy Murray spoke on Friday of "almost like little divots" appearing on Centre Court while French player Kristina Mladenovic found fault with Court 18, hours after American Bethanie Mattek-Sands seriously injured her knee on Court 17.

title: Wimbledon 2018: Roger Federer delivers shot-making masterclass to reach round three
description: The Swiss champion was at his breath-taking best as he crafted 48 exquisite winners during a 90-minute masterclass that seemed more an exhibition of his shot-making than a charge towards a record ninth Wimbledon title.

title: Australian Open 2019: ‘Vote for me!’ says political animal Madison Keys
description: Under pressure from players, the WTA made a number of rule changes in December including allowing tour members returning from maternity leave to have protected rankings for up to three years.

title: Nick Kyrgios denies kneeling in protest against US President Donald Trump
description: Nick Kyrgios denied that his kneeling down gesture before his Laver Cup clash against Roger Federer was part of similar protests against US President Donald Trump.

title: Wimbledon 2016: Serena Williams toils to scrappy opening victory
description: Serena Williams moved one step closer of winning her 22nd Grand Slam beating Amra Sadikovic 6-2 6-4 on Tuesday.

title: Three Indians qualify for Asian Junior Tennis meet
description: Denton Ho of Hong kong, Akanit Pumjit and Kasidit Tha Samrej, both natives of Thailand, also qualified for the main draw.

title: French Open 2018, Day 10 Highlights: Marco Cecchinato stuns Novak Djokovic, Dominic Thiem, Madison Keys, Sloane Stephens into semis
description: French Open 2018: Dominic Thiem set up a semifinal with Marco Cecchinato, who shocked Novak Djokovic, while in women's singles, it will be a 2017 US Open final repeat with Sloane Stephens taking on Madison Keys.

title: Sania Mirza – Martina Hingis enter last four of WTA Finals
description: Sania Mirza and Martina Hingis got the better of the Chinese Taipei's Chang sister in straight sets to advance.

title: Merciless Gael Monfils hands Stefanos Tsitsipas lesson in Sofia
description: Gael Monfils, who has slipped to 33 in the world rankings after a series of injuries, looked in ominously good form as he took his place in the last four without dropping a set this week.

title: Wimbledon 2016: Venus Williams keeps her wits about her to down Maria Sakkari
description: Venus Williams reached the Wimbledon third round with a 7-5 4-6 6-3 win over Maria Sakkari on Thursday.

title: Rafael Nadal withdraws from Roger’s cup, Cincinati open due to wrist injury
description: Rafael Nadal's title defence looks in jeopardy after he ruled himself out of the Roger's cup in Toronto.

title: AITA weren’t interested in creating a system, a culture: Somdev Devvarman
description: Injuries had forced Somdev Devvarman, who retired on Sunday, to be away for long periods and had brought his ATP ranking to 909 by the end of the 2016 season.

title: Heavyweights sign in
description: Defending champion Wawrinka, five-time winner Serena and four-time hero Djokovic advance with little fuss.

title: Women’s game in good shape despite Maria Sharapova upset of Simona Halep
description: Eight women began the U.S. Open with a chance to become world number one, an unprecedented situation which has added excitement to an already open draw. Patrick Mouratoglou said the vacuum at the top is only temporary and is caused by the absence of Serena Williams.

title: Male coaches continue to dominate women’s game
description: The highest-ranked player with a female coach is Jelena Ostapenko, who is trained by Anabel Medina Garrigues. Women players spend years traveling around the world and once they retire many choose to have a family rather than going into coaching.

title: Aisam-Ul-Haq Qureshi to skip the India-Pak Davis Cup tie in protest after shift in venue
description: Qureshi goes further to express his disappointment in his former doubles partner Rohan Bopanna, with whom he had promoted the ‘Stop war start tennis’ campaign.

title: Davis Cup: Down twice in two days, Leander Paes-Rohan Bopanna return to lift India
description: Indian duo record a dramatic come-from-behind win over Serbia to keep India's hopes alive in World Group.

title: Ambitious Rafael Nadal will not play before Wimbledon
description: French Open champion Rafael Nadal said he will play no grass court warm-up tournaments ahead of Wimbledon but is confident he can mount a challenge for a third title in southwest London.

title: Wimbledon 2018: Angelique Kerber, like Serena Williams, is on the comeback trail
description: Germany's Angelique Kerber, who will try to prevent Serena Williams winning an eighth Wimbledon title on Saturday, never went away but she too is making a comeback of sorts.

title: US Open champion Naomi Osaka dominant on return to action in Japan
description: Playing in her first tournament since winning the U.S. Open, Naomi Osaka impressed her Japanese fans with a powerful 6-2, 6-1 win over Dominika Cibulkova to reach the quarterfinals of the Pan Pacific Open.

title: Prajnesh Gunneswaran fights his way into final of Pune Challenger
description: Fourth seed Prajnesh will now fight it out with Swedish third seed Elias Ymer, who sent packing Canadian Brayden Schnur 6-3 3-6 6-3 in the other semifinal.

title: Wimbledon 2018: Rafael Nadal, Novak Djokovic, Kei Nishikori progress but end of road for Alexander Zverev, Nick Kyrgios
description: Rafael Nadal was kept on Centre Court longer than he would have liked but that did not stop him from putting baby-faced Alex de Minaur firmly in his place with a 6-1 6-2 6-4 win in the third round

title: Rafael Nadal steamrolls Juan Martin Del Potro, reaches 11th French Open final
description: Rafael Nadal left Juan Martin Del Potro trailing in a cloud of Parisian clay dust to set up a final against Dominic Thiem.

title: Australian Open: Rafael Nadal shrugs off injury concerns, pays tribute to Andy Murray
description: Of the many banged-up players on tour, Rafael Nadal may be the most able to empathise with Andy Murray, having spent long periods on the sidelines with serious knee problems.

title: Miami Open: Roberto Bautista Agut beats Novak Djokovic, Nick Kyrgios out; Kontaveit ends Hsieh’s run
description: Spaniard Roberto Bautista Agut claims second win over World No. 1 Novak Djokovic this year. Elsewhere, Borna Coric toppled temperamental Nick Kyrgios after Aussie swore at fan.

title: Johanna Konta sweating on Singapore place as Svetlana Kuznetsova lurks
description: Johanna Konta attended the draw ceremony for the showpiece season-ender having reached number eight on the WTA's Road to Singapore list.

title: Novak Djokovic, Rafael Nadal set for semifinal showdown at Indian Wells
description: Rafael Nadal defeated Kei Nishikori 6-4, 6-3 to qualify for the semi-finals at the BNP Paribas Open.

title: Sumit Nagal rises above the challenges
description: With five Challenger semis and ATP 500 appearance, Indian puts aside transit, financial woes to break into top 200

title: WTA Finals: Simona Halep begins with emphatic win over US Open champion Flavia Pennetta
description: Simona Halep began her campaign with a thumping 6-0 6-3 victory over US Open champion Flavia Pennetta.

title: Andy Murray to miss Britain’s Davis Cup quarter-final
description: Andy Murray will skip the Davis Cup tie against Serbia after his Wimbledon winning exploits. Kyle Edmund and James Ward will lead Team GB in singles.

title: After warning, Nick Kyrgios lobs ‘tweener’ at Australia’s chef de mission for Rio Olympics
description: Nick Kyrgios hit back with some cheeky humour from the Madrid Open, where he hit a stunning lob between his legs against Kei Nishikori.

title: Davis Cup: Marin Cilic beats Lucas Pouille, Croatia levels France in semi-finals
description: Earlier, Richard Gasquet won the opening tie against Borna Coric in straight sets to heap the pressure on the big-serving Cilic.

title: French Open 2016: Kristina Mladenovic, Caroline Garcia fire up home crowd in women’s doubles win
description: In a see-saw first set the French fifth seeds led 5-0 before seventh-seeded Ekaterina Makarova and Elena Vesnina clawed their way back to 5-3.

title: French Open 2016: Andy Murray overcomes ‘dropshotitis’ to down Richard Gasquet
description: Andy Murray set up a semifinal clash against defending champion Stan Wawrinka after his four set win over Richard Gasquet.

title: French Open 2016: Rain interruption was crucial, says Richard Gasquet
description: Ninth seed Richard Gasquet next faces world number two Andy Murray, who has beaten him in their four grand slam meetings.

title: Australian Open 2019: Naomi Osaka digs deep against Karolina Pliskova to set up Petra Kvitova final
description: Naomi Osaka and Petra Kvitova will vie for the World No. 1 ranking when they clash in the final on Saturday at Melbourne Park.

title: Juan Martin Del Potro sets up Auckland semi-final clash with David Ferrer
description: Juan Martin del Potro kept his Australian Open preparations on track with a 7-6(4) 6-3 win over Russia's Karen Khachanov.

title: No easy starts for top guns at the French Open 2017
description: There will be no gentle start for the favourites, with Rafa Nadal and Novak Djokovic on a semi-final collision course.

title: Rafael Nadal admits he thought he would have retired by now
description: In 2017, Rafael Nadal thought his glory days were over as he had drawn a blank at the majors in 2015 and 2016.

title: French Open 2016: Rafael Nadal, Novak Djokovic, Serena Williams headline day 3
description: Rafael Nadal begins his journey to lift the French Open trophy for the tenth time against Australian Sam Groth.

title: ATP Finals up next for Jack Sock after Paris Masters win
description: After winning the Paris Masters, Jack Sock is looking forward to end 2017 on an even more positive note at ATP Finals.

title: Rogers Cup: Andy Murray ends drought against Novak Djokovic in draining final
description: Andy Murray and Novak Djokovic embraced at the net after a three-hour battle of attrition that left them exhausted.

title: Indian challenge ends in US Open with Rohan Bopanna’s ouster
description: India's campaign at the US Open came to an end after Rohan Bopanna suffered twin defeats in both the men's and mixed doubles events in New York.

title: Milos Raonic back to avenge Queen’s Club defeat
description: Milos Raonic warned Tuesday he was determined to avenge last year's final defeat to Andy Murray.

title: Davis Cup, India vs Korea: Koreans drenched, drained and deflated
description: Debutant Ramkumar Ramanathan and Saketh Myneni deal with the conditions better on first day to give India 2-0 lead in Davis Cup.

title: US Open 2017: This has been one of the best seasons of my career, says Rafael Nadal
description: US Open 2017 champion Rafael Nadal described the year 2017 as one of the best of his career after winning a third title in New York and 16th Grand Slamby beating South Africa's world number 32 Kevin Anderson 6-3 6-3 6-4 in a one-sided final.

title: Sania Mirza-Ivan Dodig through to Australian Open mixed doubles final
description: Sania Mirza and Ivan Dodig made their way into the Australian Open final with a 6-4, 2-6, 10-5 win over Aussie pairing of Sam Stosur and Sam Groth.

title: Jelena Ostapenko eagerly waits for idol Serena Williams’ return
description: While other rivals might be looking to capitalise on 35-year-old Serena Williams' absence, Jelena Ostapenko thinks otherwise. Ostapenko says that Williams is her idol and she hopes to play the Australian Open champion someday.

title: Wimbledon 2019: Roger Federer, Serena Williams move on; Angelique Kerber exits
description: Defending women's champion Angelique Kerber went out in the second round of Wimbledon 2019 in what was the biggest upset of Thursday.

title: French Open 2017: Garbine Muguruza begins title defence by taking out Francesca Schiavone
description: Garbine Muguruza began her title defence at French Open in spectacular fashion to easily get past former champion Francesca Schiavone.

title: Wimbledon 2018: No change in scheduling policy despite calls for equality
description: Calls to give more prominence to the women’s singles competition at Wimbledon were dismissed by chief executive Richard Lewis on the opening day of the grasscourt major on Monday.

title: This is the best Davis Cup win for me in doubles, says Leander Paes
description: Paes and Bopanna overcame a two-set deficit to beat Zimonjic and Bojolzac in a thrilling five-setter.

title: After detour, Ankita Raina takes the right turn
description: Wading through several snags and blocks, the world No 253 Ankita Raina's career is finally heading in a promising direction.

title: Rain delays Miami Open start at new Hard Rock home
description: Rain wiped out the opening day play at the Miami Open on Tuesday, delaying the start of the tournament at its new Hard Rock Stadium home.

title: US Open 2016: Solid Petra Kvitova battles into third round
description: In steamy conditions, Petra Kvitova, seeded 14th, escaped a first set tiebreak and then broke twice in the second for the win.

title: Davis Cup shake-up as ITF unveils World Cup of Tennis
description: In the current format employed since 1981, 16 World Group nations take part in a knockout competition over three weekends in February, July and September before the final in November.

title: Wimbledon 2016: Dan Evans wins, faces Roger Federer next
description: Dan Evans, who before this year had never won a match in the main draw of Wimbledon, will face Roger Federer next.

title: Wimbledon 2017: Plain sailing for Roger Federer, Novak Djokovic to move into second round
description: Roger Federer and Novak Djokovic booked their placed in the second round of Wimbledon in similar fashion - leading by a set and then in the second before their respective opponents called it quits with injury.

title: Struggling Andy Murray puzzled after early Rome exit
description: Andy Murray had his most successful season on clay last year, winning one out of three finals.

title: Australian Open 2019: Lucas Pouille beats odds and Milos Raonic to reach maiden semis
description: Lucas Pouille exited in the first round in his five previous appearances at Melbourne Park and his quarter-final matchup was against an opponent who he had been unable to take a set off in three meetings.

title: Top seed Simona Halep survives scare, Amanda Anisimova earns 4th round spot
description: Simona Halep was outplayed by American Dolehide in the first set but slowly exerted her authority and, after surviving a second-set tiebreak, gradually wore down the tiring teen to secure victory.

title: French Open 2017: Ten talking points – brutal Rafael Nadal; Jelena Ostapenko, Rohan Bopanna’s first and more
description: French Open 2017 saw singles winners in Rafael Nadal - winning his tenth title in Paris - and Jelena Svitolina - winning just her first title. There was reason to celebrate for India too with Rohan Bopanna winning the mixed doubles title with Gabriela Dabrowski.

title: Novak Djokovic survives scare, Andy Murray cruises at Shanghai Masters semifinals
description: Despite his rash of unforced errors - he finished with 37, including six double faults - Novak Djokovic remained composed.

title: Naomi Osaka wins 10th straight match to power into Tokyo final
description: Naomi Osaka's victory in front of an expectant home crowd was her 10th in a row and did not look in doubt from the moment she pounded down a huge ace with her first serve of the match.

title: Australian Open: Venus Williams talks down possible Serena final showdown
description: Venus Williams is not prepared to even countenance the suggestion she could meet Serena after she advanced to quarters with a 6-3 7-5 win over Mona Barthel.

title: Maria Sharapova receives wild card into pre-Wimbledon event
description: Maria Sharapova is guaranteed a spot in qualifying for Wimbledon but still hopes to get into the main draw for the Grand Slam with a wildcard.

title: Eugenie Bouchard nosedive continues, ousted in first round of Rogers Cup
description: Eugenie Bouchard's mid-season nosedive continued on Tuesday as the Canadian was swept aside 6-3 6-4 by Croatian qualifier Donna Vekic despite having home advantage and the backing of an excited crowd in a first round clash at the Rogers Cup.

title: Wannabe posterboy of world tennis, Darko Grncarov is an imposter
description: Not since Alexander, had a Macedonian managed to accrue such worldwide fame. Then came Darko — the infamous.

title: Garbine Muguruza pulls out of Stuttgart Open due to injury
description: Garbine Muguruza was forced to retire with a back injury during her round of 16 match against Anastasia Pavlyuchenkova at the Stuttgart Open on Thursday.

title: Novak Djokovic beats Alexander Zverev in straight sets, reaches ATP Finals semis
description: Novak Djokovic will finish second in the Tokyo Group and with Rafael Nadal finishing second in the London Group, they have avoided a semi-final clash at the ATP Finals in London.

title: Australian Open 2019: Ramkumar Ramanathan, Ankita Raina make winning start; Karman Kaur Thandi exits qualifiers
description: The only other Indian in the singles qualifying draw - Prajnesh Gunneswaran - takes court on Wednesday against Croatia's Viktor Galovic.

title: Victoria Azarenka calls for more facilities for WTA’s mums
description: Victoria Azarenka wants to see more child-friendly tournaments on the WTA Tour, the former world number one returned to action last month after giving birth to son Leo in December and will soon be joined on the Tour by mum-to-be Serena Williams.

title: Davis Cup: India to host Italy on grass in Kolkata
description: Kolkata was chosen as the venue only after the All India Tennis Association (AITA) secured two key exemptions from the International Tennis Federation (ITF).

title: Wimbledon 2018: Angelique Kerber reaches final as Jelena Ostapenko self-destructs
description: Germany's Angelique Kerber proved too solid for error-strewn Latvian Jelena Ostapenko as she reached her second Wimbledon final with a 6-3 6-3 victory on Thursday.

title: Juan Martin Del Potro unlikely to be fit for Australian Open
description: Former US Open champion Juan Marti Del Potro also cast doubt on whether he would play in the Davis Cup first round tie.

title: Agnieszka Radwanska lifts her 18th WTA title
description: Agnieszka Radwanska did not drop a set in her run to the title and Saturday's triumph will increase her confidence ahead of the Australian Open.

title: Nick Kyrgios has the talent to be the best, says Rod Laver
description: Nick Kyrgios, 21, will return to tournament play at the Australian Open later this month.

title: Madrid Open: Novak Djokovic forced to put up a fight against Nicolas Almagro
description: Novak Djokovic was made to sweat by Nicolas Almagro in Madrid Open but eventually overcame the Spaniard 6-1 4-6, 7-5.

title: Maria Sharapova eyes more grand slam glory
description: Maria Sharapova will not settle for lower-tier titles after making her comeback last year and the former world number one is determined to add to her five grand slam crowns.

title: Davis Cup: Ramkumar Ramanathan, Prajnesh Gunneswaran suffer defeats as Serbia lead India 2-0
description: Ramkumar Ramanthan battled hard before losing 6-3 4-6 6-7(2) 2-6 to Djere in the opening singles which lasted three hours and 11 minutes on the indoor clay court.

title: Victoria Azarenka’s coach confident ahead of US Open final
description: Victoria Azarenka came back from a one-set deficit to topple 23-time Grand Slam winner Serena Williams in their semifinal match inside Arthur Ashe Stadium on Thursday.

title: Wimbledon 2014: Novak Djokovic advances to fourth round
description: Djokovic overcame a hard fall in the third set to advance to the fourth round with a win over Gilles Simon.

title: Roger Federer on top of the world with his Australian Open trophy
description: Roger Federer still seems to be celebrating his Australian Open triumph earlier in the year.

title: It has been a great year for me: Sania Mirza
description: Sania Mirza and Martina Hingis have won four titles this season.

title: Wimbledon 2019: Karolina Pliskova sees off tricky Hsieh Su-wei, Caroline Wozniacki faces her end
description: On Wimbledon Day 5, former world number one Karolina Pliskova served superbly to beat Hsieh Su-wei 6-3 2-6 6-4, while Caroline Wozniacki fell to a 6-4 6-2 defeat to Zhang Shuai on Friday.

title: Davis Cup record is for all of India, says Leander Paes
description: Leander Paes broke the 46-year-old record of Italian legend Nicola Pietrangeli, by winning his 43rd Davis Cup doubles match.

title: French Open 2018: Rafa Nadal marches past Maximilian Marterer and into quarterfinals
description: Rafa Nadal continued his birthday celebrations by moving into the French Open quarter-finals on Monday, beating a determined Maximilian Marterer 6-3 6-2 7-6(4).

title: Wimbledon 2017: Icy dips for ailing hip helps Andy Murray stay mobile
description: Andy Murray suffered an injury scare in the week before Wimbledon as he pulled out of two exhibition matches at Hurlingham due to a sore hip but the extra effort worked wonders as he cruised to a comfortable win over Alexander Bublik without showing any signs of injury troubles.

title: French Open 2020: Karolina Pliskova advances, Jennifer Brady ousted by teenager
description: Karolina Pliskova, who retired in the final in Rome with injury before coming to Paris, sealed her match against Mayar Sherif with an ace and will next meet 2017 champion Jelena Ostapenko.

title: Wimbledon: We have feelings and it is not easy sometimes, says Bruno Soares
description: Bruno Soares, who got a warning from the umpire, said that the warning was unnecessary as tempers get frayed during the heat of competition.

title: US Open: Novak Djokovic opts for home over hotel, reaches Round 3
description: Most players competing at Flushing Meadows amid the coronavirus pandemic this year opted for the official tournament hotel options.

title: Australian Open 2018: Simona Halep reaps reward for aggressive approach
description: Simona Halep prevailed in the semifinal clash against Angelique Kerber, beating the German by 6-3 4-6 9-7 on Rod Laver Arena to reach her first Australian Open final.

title: US Open 2016: Angelique Kerber beats Petra Kvitova, enters quarters
description: Kerber won 6-3, 7-5 on Sunday in a matchup of left-handers to set up a meeting with last year's runner-up, Roberta Vinci.

title: Wimbledon: Nick Kyrgios bares his soul after loss to Andy Murray
description: Nick Kyrgios has said that he doesn't love Tennis and is not so sure he wants to fix that.

title: Kristyna beats Karolina in battle of Pliskova twins at Birmingham Classic
description: The twins were scheduled to play earlier this year in Doha, but Karolina achieved a walkover following Kristyna's withdrawal. The sisters now have a 1-1 head-to-head on the professional tour.

title: Milos Raonic beaten by Mikhail Youzhny in St. Petersburg Open
description: Mikhail Youzhny toughed out a 10-minute final game to cap the match and his first win over a top-10 player in more than two years.

title: Wimbledon 2016: Indian challenge ends as Leander Paes-Martina Hingis out of mixed doubles
description: Heather Watson and Henri Kontinen pair playing their first match of the tournament knocked out 16th seeded Leander Paes and Martina Hingis.

title: Daria Kasatkina stuns Caroline Wozniacki to reach St Petersburg semi-finals
description: World number one Caroline Wozniacki suffered her first defeat since lifting the Australian Open trophy when she was edged out 7-6(2) 6-3 by Russia's Daria Kasatkina.

title: My child will have surname Mirza Malik, says Sania Mirza
description: Sania Mirza spoke about her personal experiences of gender bias, where she has heard some of her relatives telling her parents that they should have had a son so that the family name "goes ahead".

title: Serena Williams announces engagement to Reddit co-founder Alexis Ohanian
description: Serena Williams announced her engagement to Alexis Ohanian, co-founder of Reddit, via, naturally, a Reddit post.

title: Yuki Bhambri jumps to 159 in ATP rankings
description: Following his impressive Washington performance, Yuki Bhambri now has 365 points while Ramkumar Ramanathan has 308 points. Prajnesh Gunneswaran (213), Sumit Nagal (266) and N Sriram Balaji (297) are the next three Indians to round off the top 5.

title: Refreshed Angelique Kerber relishing emotional return to Wimbledon’s grass
description: It is not new territory for the 31-year-old former world number one who on two other occasions arrived for the start of a Grand Slam having won it the year before.

title: US Open: Andrea Petkovic stuns Petra Kvitova, Simona Halep suffers another early exit
description: World number 88 Petkovic was the better player in the biggest points, breaking the twice Grand Slam champion three times and committing 15 fewer unforced errors on a sun-soaked Louis Armstrong Stadium court.

title: Serena Williams could face Maria Sharapova in fourth round at French Open 2018
description: Serena Williams could face Maria Sharapova in the fourth round of the French Open on her return to Grand Slam tennis from maternity leave.

title: Novak Djokovic in, Rafael Nadal out for Serbia-Spain Davis Cup
description: Rafael Nadal will miss Spain's Davis Cup quarterfinal against Serbia and there are chances of Novak Djokovic making a comeback.

title: Hope more youngsters take up sports as career: Sania Mirza
description: Sania hoped that young girls and women would be inspired to take up sports as a career.

title: US Open 2016: Will Novak Djokovic play a full semi-final against Gael Monfils?
description: Novak Djokovic has been needed to complete only two of five matches at US Open because of injuries to three foes.

title: Prajnesh Gunneswaran knocked out of Maharashtra Open
description: Few weeks after making the ATP Challenger final in Pune, Prajnesh Gunneswaran exited the ATP 250 tournament in the first round.

title: Davis Cup: India hope for a high against Italy on grass
description: Prajnesh Gunneswaran will face Andreas Seppi in first singles; visitors pick lower-ranked Matteo Berrettini over Marco Cecchinato.

title: US Open 2017: Opinions divided on Maria Sharapova as Slam return looms
description: Rivals remain divided over Maria Sharapova as she prepares to return to Grand Slam tennis tomorrow at the US Open after a 15-month doping ban.

title: AITA terminates Vijay Amritraj backed CTL contract over non-payment
description: All India Tennis Association (AITA) on Tuesday terminated the contract of Vijay Amritraj's Champions Tennis League due to non-payment of annual fee of Rs 30 lakh for the 2016 season.

title: Angelique Kerber set for sustained success after Wimbledon 2018 title
description: The changes Angelique Kerber has made on the court helped her win a first Wimbledon title. She believes the changes she made off the court will ensure her second coming as a dominant force in the women's game endures.

title: Kristina Mladenovic faces Shelby Rogers test to break new ground in Paris
description: Shelby Rogers won their only previous encounter 6-1 6-1 in New Haven in 2016 and was also a French Open quarter-finalist a year ago, while 13th seed Mladenovic has never progressed past the third round in eight visits to Roland Garros prior to this year.

title: Andy Murray ready to work overtime in Barcelona to stay at top
description: Andy Murray took a late entry into Barcelona Open after an early defeat to Albert Ramos-Vinolas in Monte Carlo last week.

title: Rafael Nadal pulls out of Cincinnati, scuttling ‘Big 4’ reunion
description: Rafael Nadal, Roger Federer, Novak Djokovic and Andy Murray haven't played in the same tournament in more than a year.

title: Ashwini Ponappa focussing on being fit and ready for Olympic qualification
description: Ashwini Ponappa is aware that the road to Olympic qualification will be a tough one as she and her women's doubles partner N Sikki Reddy will have to rack up ranking points ahead of the April 30 deadline.

title: Elina Svitolina beats Angelique Kerber and will face Caroline Wozniacki in Dubai final
description: Angelique Kerber struggled with a knee injury during a 6-3, 7-6 (3) loss to Elina Svitolina in the semifinals of Dubai Championships.

title: Kei Nishikori out of Australian Open with elbow injury
description: The world No. 13, who has not played since a third-round loss at the U.S. Open, required minor elbow surgery in the off-season and will miss the grand slam Down Under, starting from January 20.

title: Victoria Azarenka’s gesture to injured opponent wins hearts
description: After an emotional scene in which she was comforted by Azarenka on the court, the Russian was unable to continue and retired from the match after one hour and 16 minutes of an intense battle.

title: DLTA defends evening timing for Davis Cup tie against Spain
description: DLTA defended its decision saying the aim is to make the event more accessible to the tennis fans and save Indian players from cramping.

title: Novak Djokovic breezes into third round, Rafa Nadal works hard for win
description: Novak Djokovic and Rafa Nadal post contrasting wins in the second round of Shanghai Open.

title: Wimbledon 2018 Day 6 Tennis Highlights: Djokovic, Nadal advance; Zverev, Halep out
description: Wimbledon 2018 Day 6 Tennis Highlights: Novak Djokovic and Rafael Nadal advance while Alexander Zverev and Simona Halep ousted.

title: Maturing Nick Kyrgios knocks Stanislas Wawrinka out of Madrid Open
description: Nick Kyrgios knocked the fourth seed Stanislas Wawrinka out of the Madrid Open by 7-6(7) 7-6(2).

title: Andy Murray contemplates surgery to heal hip injury in emotional post
description: Andy Murray is forced to consider surgery to heal his hip injury. He pulled out of Brisbane International on Tuesday.

title: Australia Open 2017: Appetite for destruction helps Alexander Zverev into second round
description: The 19-year old German advanced to the second round after beating Robin Haase by 6-2 3-6 5-7 6-3 6-2.

title: Wimbledon: For best, Novak Djokovic, rest before quest
description: Djokovic only got onto grass courts ten days ago, in contrast to his rivals in build up to Wimbledon defence.

title: US Open 2018 Women’s Final Highlights: Naomi Osaka makes history, beats Serena Williams in straight sets
description: US Open 2018 Women's Final Highlights: Naomi Osaka became the first Japanese player to win a grand slam title by beating Serena Williams 6-2, 6-4 in a controversy filled final.

title: Bengaluru Open comes back with bigger prize purse
description: India is only the fourth country in Asia to host the highest category Challenger tournament, which offers 100 ranking points and a prize purse of USD 18,000 to the winner.

title: Simona Halep outlasts determined Kristina Mladenovic to retain Madrid title
description: The third seed produced her best tennis in the decider after edging the first set and being pegged back in the second by 14th seed Mladenovic.

description: Day 7 of the Australian Open saw exits for both top seeds in men's and women's singles draw as Andy Murray and Angelique Kerber bowed out.

title: CoCo Vandeweghe, an all-or-nothing striker, on strong run at Australian Open

title: Rafael Nadal begins new era without mentor uncle Toni in Australia

title: Wimbledon 2019: Victoria Azarenka criticises gender ‘inequality’ in tournament schedules
description: Azarenka, who was knocked out of Wimbledon by Simona Halep on Friday, said the time slots and courts allocated to matches was the next big fight in the battle for gender equality in tennis.

title: Wimbledon 2016: One five-setter too many! Milos Raonic beats Roger Federer to reach final
description: Roger Federer was involved in a five-setter against Marin Cilic in the quarter-final and then again against Milos Raonic in the semi-final.

title: Wimbledon 2016: Exhausted Juan Martin del Potro bows out to Lucas Pouille
description: Trailing by two sets to one when bad light stopped the third-round tussle on Saturday, Del Potro looked jaded as the fourth set sped away from him.

title: International Tennis Federation defends US Open chair umpire Carlos Ramos
description: The International Tennis Federation (ITF) has given its backing to chair umpire Carlos Ramos who Serena Williams called a "liar" and a "thief" during her U.S. Open final.

title: ATP NextGen Finals: South Korea’s Hyeon Chung taking new rules in his stride in Milan
description: Hyeon Chung begun the NextGen Finals with two wins in two matches. He beat Denis Shapovalov on Tuesday and Andrey Rublev on Wednesday.

title: Vijay Amritraj expresses concern at lack of system in Indian tennis
description: In the Davis Cup, India have not able to go past the play-offs in last four years, losing to Serbia, the Czech Republic, Spain and Canada in last four years

title: Australian Open 2019: Sports fraternity congratulates Naomi Osaka on creating history
description: Naomi Osaka defeated Czech Republic's Petra Kvitova 7-6(2) 5-7 6-4 to win the Australian Open title on Saturday.

title: Australian Open: Kei Nishikori continues to fly Asia flag in ‘home’ Grand Slam
description: Kei Nishikori said Asia still struggling to produce more players capable of ending their grand slam men's singles drought.

title: David Goffin beats Richard Gasquet to reach Japan Open semifinals
description: David Goffin, the runner-up here last year, has been on a winning run in Asia after claiming his first title in three years last weekend at Shenzhen, China.

description: Yuki Bhambri had set up the second round clash with world number 22 and defending champion Gael Monfils after his first round opponent had to retire. With this win, Bhambri, who is ranked at 200, has qualified for the pre-quarterfinals.

description: Sloane Stephens, recently back from a foot injury that kept her from the courts for a year, showed her defensive prowess in her defeat of Venus Williams, while Madison Keys hit winner after winner to crush CoCo Vandeweghe in the other semifinal.

title: Leander Paes sacking sad but step in right direction: Jaidip Mukerjea

title: French Open 2018: Benoit Paire falls short, but Kei Nishikori faces another test
description: Beaten 6-3 2-6 4-6 6-2 6-3 by Japan's Kei Nishikori, Benoit Paire showed flashes of brilliance and, at two sets to one up, large sections of the crowd had started to believe.

title: On 32nd birthday, Sania Mirza hits the gym soon after giving birth to baby Izhaan

title: Sania Mirza- Barbora Strycova in final of Apia International
description: Sania Mirza and Barbora Strycova thrashed America's Vania King and Yaroslava Shvedova from Kazakhstan 6-1 6-2.

title: Australian Open 2018: The next Novak Djokovic? Chung Hyeon serves notice in South Korea

title: AITA brings back Zeeshan Ali in selection committee, removes Vishal Uppal
description: Rohit Rajpal, who was already in the panel, was named as the new chief while Nandan Bal and Balram Singh were retained.

title: Serena Williams eases into Cincinnati quarters

title: Not a big deal to hire Carlos Moya as coach, says pain-hit Rafa Nadal
description: Injury-hit Rafa Nadal, 30, said he hadn't played without pain for years but that he remained optimistic of challenging for big titles again.

title: Ryan Harrison beats Nikoloz Basilashvili 6-1, 6-4 to win Memphis Open
description: This victory is expected to move Ryan Harrison to No. 43 in the world, matching his career-best ranking reached in July 2012.

title: Yuki Bhambri loses in semifinal of Houston Cup
description: Yuki Bhambri, top-seeded Indian, lost 2-6 6-4 5-7 to his unseeded rival Wil Spencer in the hard court event.

title: Spain’s golden era is fading but Feliciano Lopez stays positive

description: The crowd were in for exhilarating action at the Chennai Open on Sunday for the second round of the qualifiers.

title: Davis Cup: Spain ready for yawn tennis against India in World Group Playoff
description: Mismatch in class between India and visitors is set to make the Davis Cup encounter a one-sided affair.

title: French Open 2016: Andy Murray teeters on the brink, Stan Wawrinka pushed to fifth
description: Defending champion Stan Wawrinka had to battle hard before beating Lukas Rosol 4-6 6-1 3-6 6-3 6-4 in first round.

description: Former world number one Serena Williams was knocked out of the French Open in the third round following a 6-2 7-5 defeat to fellow American Sofia Kenin.

title: Wimbledon 2014: Maria Sharapova’s wait extends

description: Garbine Muguruza knows she can beat Serena Williams on the big stage.

title: Novak Djokovic hoping to put struggles behind him at Wimbledon
description: A third-round defeat to Sam Querrey last year at the All England Club was the stunning start of a prolonged slump, a slump which Djokovic hopes he is finally on the way to ending after winning his second title of the year in Eastbourne on Saturday.

title: Roger Federer hopes to play for two-three more years
description: Roger Federer and Belinda Bencic begin play against Britain, represented by Heather Watson and Dan Evans, on Monday in the Hopman Cup.

description: Kiki Bertens of the Netherlands beat Croatia's Donna Vekic 7-6(2) 6-4 to win the St Petersburg Ladies Trophy on Sunday and claim her eighth WTA singles title.

title: French Open 2016: Richard Gasquet and Nick Kyrgios relishing Paris showdown
description: Friday's meeting will be their seventh, the best two having been played at Wimbledon in the last two years.

title: Davis Cup row may push young players away from national duty, feels Saketh Myneni
description: The undercurrent of India’s upcoming Davis Cup tie against Pakistan and the customary drama that comes with it doesn't stay unnoticed or unspoken.

title: Jo-Wilfried Tsonga, Milos Raonic reach semi-final of Lyon Open

description: India’s highest ranked women’s singles player Ankita Raina had just pulled off her first win over a top 100 player, in a gruelling contest that lasted two hours and 49 minutes against 2011 US Open champion Samantha Stosur.

description: Mats Wilander believes Nick Kyrgios can become the best tennis player in the world without gruelling trips to the gym and endless hours of practice -- providing he keeps playing doubles. Kyrgios suffered a second round exit, losing 5-7 6-4 6-1 6-2 to Kevin Anderson.

description: Fabio Fognini got the Foro Italico crowd fired up Wednesday with a 6-4, 1-6, 6-3 win over sixth-seeded Dominic Thiem in the second round of the Italian Open.

title: Australian Open 2018: Simona Halep survives date with Destanee Aiava in opening round
description: Simona Halep was forced to save two set points at 5-2 down and come from 3-1 down to rescue the tiebreak to win the first set against the 17-year old Destanee Aiava.

title: Novak Djokovic beats Kei Nishikori in Rogers Cup final
description: The latest victory was a 30th ATP World Tour Masters 1000 title for Novak Djokovic.

title: Wimbledon 2019: Serena Williams “available” for mixed doubles as Andy Murray seeks partner
description: Serena Williams suggested that she likes "to be tongue-in-cheek" after suggesting her availability to become a mixed-doubles partner for the recently returning, two-time Wimbledon champion Andy Murray.

title: Serena Williams may lack intimidation factor, says Chris Evert
description: Serena Williams, who gave birth to a baby girl in September, has said she's planning to defend her title at the Australian Open in January.

title: Sania Mirza equals career-best fifth rank in world
description: Sania Mirza had achieved the top-5 rank last year too in July.

description: World number 18 Madison Keys, who beat Japan's Nao Hibino in the first round, told tennis.com that Petra Kvitova's comeback made her emotional and believes that the Czech's strength on grass could see her clinch a third Wimbledon title.

description: Denis Istomin, who knocked out Novak Djokovic in the second round lost to Grigor Dimitrov  2-6 7-6(2) 6-2 6-1.

title: Serena Williams, NFL players to compete in charity virtual tennis event
description: The “Stay at Home Slam” will be streamed Sunday at 1:30 AM IST on Facebook Gaming and on the tennis Facebook page of the company coordinating the tournament, IMG.

title: Favourites thwarted in US Open wheelchair singles events
description: Two men who sought history-making Grand Slams in wheelchair tennis were thwarted at the U.S. Open this weekend.

title: ATP announces independent review of anti-corruption unit to ‘restore public confidence’
description: ATP's decision comes in wake of allegations that officials had failed to properly investigate suspected cases of match-fixing.

title: Leander Paes’ mantra for kids: Work a little extra
description: Leander Paes shared tips on how to play the game and encouraged them to “think like champions".

title: WTA Finals debutants ready to rock in Singapore
description: Elina Svitolina's appearance will feel like her graduation after playing in the last two WTA Elite Trophy tournaments in Zhuhai, China.

title: Aus Open 2016: Serena Williams makes it 18-0 against Maria Sharapova, enters semis
description: Serena Williams has reached the last four at Melbourne Park on six previous occasions and gone on to win the title every time.

title: Coaching stint with Andy Murray would not last long, feels John McEnroe

title: US Open 2019: Rafael Nadal wins five-hour battle to lift crown for fourth time

title: Serena Williams beat Naomi Osaka to advance to Rogers Cup semifinals, Bianca Andreescu stuns Karolina Pliskova
description: Serena Williams advanced to the Rogers Cup semifinals Friday night, beating soon-to-be-top-ranked Naomi Osaka of Japan 6-3, 6-4 at breezy at York University.

title: American teen Amanda Anisimova stuns Wang Qiang in Miami
description: Amanda Anisimova beat China's Wang Qiang 6-3 1-6 6-2 at the Miami Open on Tuesday to set up a second-round clash with Spanish third seed Garbine Muguruza.

title: ITF seeks India’s view after Pakistan appeal, AITA stays firm on security concerns
description: The ITF had taken the decision on November 4, paying heed to AITA's repeated requests for a neutral venue, which prompted the PTF's to challenge the move. In response, the ITF reached out to AITA on Monday.

title: Australian Open Day 10: Simona Halep, Garbine Muguruza to meet in semifinals
description: The two-times Grand Slam champion had not lost a set in her previous two meetings with Kontaveit and the quarter-final was no different, the 28th seed managing just one breakpoint on former world number one Halep's serve.

title: Juan Martin Del Potro upsets Tomas Berdych in 1st round at Cincinnati
description: The 30th-ranked del Potro shook off a first-set loss, jumping out to a 4-1 lead in the second set before settling for a win in the tiebreak, which he led 5-0 and clinched with an ace.

title: US Open: Martin Hingis’ return ends on a low; Ekaterina Makarova-Elena Vesnina win doubles title
description: Makarova, Vesnina collect their second grand slam together having also lifted the French Open trophy in 2013.

title: Sania Mirza’s formula for success
description: Sania Mirza has found a measure of success in her charge towards parity when partnering Barbora Strycova.

title: Roger Federer beats Stefanos Tsitsipas in Dubai to claim 100th title
description: Roger Federer claimed the 100th ATP title of his career by beating 20-year-old Greek Stefanos Tsitsipas 6-4 6-4 in the final of the Dubai Duty Free Tennis Championships on Saturday.

title: US Open: Upsets continue in women’s draw, Serena Williams, Novak Djokovic advance
description: The shock of the day was delivered by the little-known Krunic, who stung the unsteady Kvitova 6-4 6-4.

title: Russia’s Daria Kasatkina, Germany’s Julia Goerges reach Kremlin Cup final
description: Kasatkina will be joined in the final by seventh seed Goerges, who destabilised Russia's Natalia Vikhlyantseva by breaking her serve in the first game before going on to win the match 6-2 2-6 7-5.

title: Australian Open: Leaner, mature Naomi Osaka stays grounded in Melbourne
description: Melbourne Park remains a special place for Naomi Osaka as the Australian Open was the first Grand Slam where she got into the main draw through the qualifiers in 2016.

title: French Open: On song Stan Wawrinka overcomes Jo-Wilfried Tsonga to reach final
description: Wawrinka overcame strong resistance from Tsonga to win 6-3 6-7 7-6 6-4 and reach the final.

title: After knee gives way, Li Na gives up career
description: She hasn’t played since a third-round defeat at Wimbledon, withdrawing from the U.S. Open citing a knee injury.

title: Stan Wawrinka survives scare to advance in Toronto
