title: Need to have a system in place to get singles champions, says Rohan Bopanna
description: French Open return champion Rohan Bopanna, who won the mixed doubles title with Canadian partner Gabriela Dabrowski, said on Thursday that to create champions in singles, the country needs to build a system in place at the grassroot level.

title: Venus Williams, Sloane Stephens shine in cloudy Labour Day weekend at US Open
description: American women continued to shine on a grey Labor Day weekend as the resurgent Venus Williams and Sloane Stephens fought their way into the quarter-finals of the U.S. Open on Sunday.

title: Roger Federer beats Nick Kyrgios to retain World No 1 ranking
description: Roger Federer, 36, will return to top of the ATP rankings for the sixth time in his career and begin a record 310th week at the summit of the men's game.

title: No. 1 rankings has taken huge effort in last few months: Andy Murray
description: Andy Murray became the oldest man since 1974 to reach the top of the rankings for the first time last month.

title: Davis Cup: A couple of doubles headaches for India, Spain
description: Davis Cup: While Leander Paes will be without Rohan Bopanna by his side, Spain have formidable options for Saturday.

title: Prajnesh Gunneswaran’s Australian Open first round match rescheduled due to rain
description: Prajnesh Gunneswaran, who entered the main draw of the men's singles event as a lucky loser in the qualifiers, was scheduled to play Ito, ranked 144th in the world on Monday.

title: Anand Amritraj’s Davis Cup journey ends where it began 43 years ago
description: Back in 1974, Anand Amritraj was a 22-year-old looking for a permanent break in the Davis Cup team.

title: Petra Kvitova cruises as favourites dominate at Stanford
description: Second seed Petra Kvitova was barely troubled in her first match at the Stanford Classic as the big-hitting Czech needed just an hour to demolish Kateryna Bondarenko 6-2 6-2 in a second round encounter on Thursday.

title: Sania Mirza recommended for Rajiv Gandhi Khel Ratna, Rohit Sharma set to get Arjuna
description: Sania Mirza is only the second tennis player after Leander Paes to be named for the top award.

title: Milos Raonic retires from match at Japan Open with calf injury
description: Milos Raonic picked up another injury Thursday and was forced to retire from his second-round match at the Japan Open.

title: India find a partner for Leander Paes
description: Vishnu Vardhan drafted in as a last-minute replacement for injured Saketh Myneni for the tie against New Zealand.

title: Novak Djokovic has not worked hard enough, says former coach Boris Becker
description: Boris Becker said Novak Djokovic's need to spend more time with his family had derailed him on the court.

title: Rafael Nadal rallies to beat Leonard Mayer in 3 sets in Barcelona Open
description: The second-ranked Nadal was coming off a loss in the semifinals of the Monte Carlo Open, when he was eliminated by Fabio Fognini.

title: Serena Williams ready for long-awaited return at Indian Wells
description: Serena Williams, who claimed a 23rd grand slam title at last year's Australian Open before hanging up her racket for the season upon discovering she was pregnant with her first child.

title: Juan Martin del Potro cuts Reilly Opelka down to size with Delray Beach win
description: Reilly Opelka won his first career title at the New York Open on Sunday but was nowhere near his best against Del Potro and looked particularly vulnerable on his second serve.

title: French Open 2017 Final: Jelena Ostapenko aiming to break through the Simona Halep wall
description: Jelena Ostapenko faces the master of defence Simona Halep in Saturday's French Open final. Ostapenko, who is looking to become the first unseeded woman to lift the title since 1933, blazed her way to the final, hitting winners and errors with reckless abandon.

title: Return to sender: Roger Federer looking forward to Serena William’s serve
description: Roger Federer is excited about the prospect of taking on his fellow tennis great on Tuesday in a Hopman Cup mixed doubles match between Switzerland and the United States.

title: Wimbledon 2017: Venus Williams preparing for Johanna Konta serving barrage
description: American veteran Venus Williams was sharpening her reactions for the barrage of big serves she can expect in her Wimbledon semi-final against British favourite Johanna Konta on Thursday, going through a relentless practise routine on the eve of battle.

title: ATP chief Chris Kermode appointed for second term
description: Chris Kermode was appointed for a second term in charge of men's tennis on Thursday, having taken over the role in January 2014.

title: French Open 2018: Serena Williams shows plenty of fight to subdue Ashleigh Barty
description: Anyone foolish enough to think motherhood would kill off Serena Williams' competitive edge got a reminder of why the 23-times Grand Slam champion is one of the all-time greats.

title: Simona Halep’s Palermo appearance in doubt after Italy’s quarantine order
description: Palermo Open will mark the first professional tennis event across the WTA and the ATP Tours since early March with action scheduled to get underway on the clay courts from August 3.

title: Wimbledon 2017: Martina Hingis-Jamie Murray win mixed doubles title
description: Martina Hingis has now won six major mixed doubles titles as well as 12 in women's doubles -- not to mention five singles. She partnered with Britain's Jamie Murray to win the title 6-4, 6-4.

title: ATP Finals: Cannot guarantee if I will be fit, says Rafael Nadal
description: Rafael Nadal is due to play David Goffin in his first match on Monday, but told reporters that his injured knee might not hold up.

title: Davis Cup: Leander Paes creates world record in India’s stunning comeback win
description: Leander Paes became the most successful doubles player in the history of Davis Cup with a record 43rd win before young guns Ramkumar Ramanathan and Prajnesh Gunneswaran pulled off the must-win rubbers.

title: Wimbledon 2016 Day 3: Where and how to catch the Grand Slam live
description: Wimbledon 2016 Day 3 Live Streaming, video, results and more from the Grand Slam.

title: Oscars 2019: Serena Williams introduces ‘A Star Is Born’ with inspiring speech
description: Serena Williams appeared on the red carpet and later presented the film "A Star Is Born" at the 2019 Academy Awards on Sunday night in Los Angeles.

title: Bethanie Mattek-Sands loses on comeback but earns warm applause at Miami Open
description: It was a far different scene the last time Bethanie Mattek-Sands was in action when she was carried off court on a stretcher screaming in pain after suffering an horrific knee injury during last year's Wimbledon.

title: Sumit Nagal to play maiden ATP 500 event, qualifies for Hamburg Open
description: Nagal has enjoyed success in the last few weeks in the Challenger circuit, where he made five semifinals in seven tournaments. He eveb recorded the biggest win of his career when he beat world number 56 Martin Klizan at Bratislava Open last month.

title: Naomi Osaka wins hearts with gesture to 15-year-old Coco Gauff after beating her in US Open
description: Naomi Osaka beat 15-year-old Coco Gauff in straight sets in the third round of the US Open on Saturday. After the match, Osaka walked up to a tearful Gauff and consoled her, asking her to do an on-court interview with her.

title: AITA wants to know reasons for Ankita Raina’s TOPS exclusion
description: Ankita may not feature in the singles competition at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics but will be a potential candidate to be in the Indian team for the next year's Asian Games.

title: Commentator Doug Adler dropped over Venus ‘gorilla’ remark
description: During an Australian Open stream, Doug Adler compared Venus Williams to a 'gorilla' although he insisted the word he used was guerrilla.

title: Wimbledon: Leander Paes-Daniel Nestor enter Rd 2
description: Paes and Nestor quelled the challenge from the Serbian pair of Victor Troicki and Dusan Lajovic.

title: Naomi Osaka passes Anastasija Sevastova test to reach Brisbane semis
description: Naomi Osaka dropped only five points in the second set and then cruised through the decider. "Maybe six months ago I wouldn't have been able to do that (come back)," the US Open champion said.

title: Vishnu Vardhan out of singles but makes doubles semis with N Sriram Balaji
description: Vishnu Vardhan was ousted from the singles event following a straight-set defeat in the second round but progressed to the doubles semifinals with compatriot N Sriram Balaji at the ATP Challenger event in China.

title: Tennis in 2016: Andy Murray makes it his year as Novak Djokovic struggles
description: Andy Murray not only took over as the top ranked player, he got past the Novak Djokovic voodoo. Serena Williams was stopped in her tracks by Angelique Kerber.

title: Queen’s Club Championships 2018: Yuki Bhambri sets up clash with Milos Raonic
description: Yuki Bhambri on Sunday qualified for the ATP 500 Fever-Tree Championships after beating America's Taylor Fritz in the second and final qualifying round in London.

title: Stan Wawrinka exits Aegon Championships after first round loss
description: Stan Wawrinka crashed out of the Aegon Championships after first round 6-2 7-6 loss to Fernando Verdasco.

title: Even without Serena Williams, Australian Open women’s field still tough
description: Without defending champion Serena Williams in the draw at the Australian Open, there's certainly an opportunity for another player  to emerge as a first-time Grand Slam champion.

title: Katerina Siniakova captures maiden title with Shenzhen Open win
description: Katerina Siniakova overcame a slow start to win her maiden WTA Tour title with a 6-3 6-4 victory over Alison Riske in the Shenzhen Open final.

title: Andy Murray to play Hurlingham exhibitions after Queen’s exit
description: Andy Murray suffered an embarrassing first-round loss against Australian world number 90 Jordan Thompson, robbing the Scot of valuable time on grass before the start of Wimbledon on July 3.

title: Griogor Dimitrov sets up last-16 clash with Juan Del Potro at Cincinnati Open
description: Grigor Dimitrov, who beat Lopez in the second round here last year, nearly broke the unseeded Spaniard three times prior to making a strong start in the tiebreak and went on to finish the match with 27 winners.

title: Prajnesh Gunneswaran top-seeded for Chennai Open ATP
description: Players from countries, including Australia, the USA, South Korea, Japan, Egypt, New Zealand, Serbia, Spain and Germany are among those expected to participate in the tournament.

title: Victoria Azarenka to miss Fed Cup final over custody battle
description: Victoria Azarenka said she was unwilling to leave her son behind in California

title: Frances Tiafoe wants to draw more black kids to tennis
description: American Frances Tiafoe has already changed the lives of his immigrant parents thanks to his tennis career and the 2019 Australian Open quarter-finalist hopes he can also inspire more black kids to take up the sport.

title: 2017 slump was key to Wimbledon title, says Angelique Kerber
description: Angelique Kerber produced a superb display to beat Serena Williams 6-3 6-3 and become the first German since Steffi Graf in 1996 to lift the Venus Rosewater Dish on Centre Court.

title: Roger Federer using SABR to devastating effect
description: Craig O'Shannessy, the analyst for the ATP Tour, believes shortening his backswing to play the SABR helped take Roger Federer’s backhand – and his backhand return - to another level. This was visible during the Australian Open final against Rafael Nadal.

title: Facing domestic violence allegations, Alexander Zverev gets Djokovic’s support
description: Novak Djokovic said tennis authorities could adopt clearer policies on domestic abuse in light of allegations made against Alexander Zverev by his ex-girlfriend Olga Sharypova.

title: Boris Becker coming to Delhi to launch footwear collection
description: Boris Becker is coming to Delhi launch a footwear named collection after him.

title: Rafa Nadal set for Toronto return before Rio 2016 Olympics
description: Rafa Nadal will miss Wimbledon after failing to recover from the wrist injury which also forced his early withdrawal from the French Open last month.

title: US Open 2018: Serena Williams survives scare from Kaia Kanepi to reach quarters
description: Next up for Serena Williams is a quarter-final meeting with eighth seeded Karolina Pliskova who advanced with a straight-forward 6-4 6-4 win over Ashleigh Barty.

title: Serena Williams’ baby bump photo sparks pregnancy speculation
description: Serena Williams got engaged to Reddit co-founder Alexi Ohanian in December.

title: Bernard Tomic offered spot in Australian Open wild card playoff
description: Bernard Tomic, 25, ranked a career high 17 last year, has slumped to 143 in the world after a miserable season in which he won only 10 of 19 matches.

title: All England grass a tonic for Bernard Tomic
description: Bernard Tomic made his grand slam breakthrough when he reached the Wimbledon quarter-finals as a qualifier in 2011.

title: Kei Nishikori ruled out of Brisbane International
description: Kei Nishikori has withdrawn from the season-opening Brisbane International tournament as he continues to recover from a wrist injury.

title: Novak Djokovic crushes Stefanos Tsitsipas to reach Paris Masters semis
description: Novak Djokovic will face Grigor Dimitrov in one semifinal at the Paris Masters. The other semifinal will be contested by the winners of Shapovalov vs Monfils and Tsonga vs Nadal.

title: Juan del Potro wins Stockholm title after 33-month drought
description: Juan Martin del Potro won the Stockholm Open, beating sixth-seeded Jack Sock 7-5, 6-1 to claim his 19th ATP tour title.

title: French Open 2017: Elina Svitolina survives scare in a rollercoaster match
description: Elina Svitolina survived a second-round scare, losing her way in the first set against Tsvetana Pironkova before serving up a rollercoaster 3-6 6-3 6-2 win. The Ukrainian struggled early on as her heavy groundstrokes fell short or wide.

title: Distracted Alexander Zverev seeks to rediscover spark
description: Alexander Zverev's slump has coincided with an ongoing legal wrangle with former manager Patricio Apey, which has left him with far more to worry about than just rocking up for his practice sessions.

title: Daniil Medvedev sees off Kei Nishikori in Barcelona to reach first claycourt final
description: Russian Daniil Medvedev reached the final of the Barcelona Open for the first time after edging out Kei Nishikori 6-4 3-6 7-5 in a tense and tight semi-final on Saturday.

title: Roger Federer reaches 11th Halle final after beating Karen Khachano
description: The 18-times grand slam champion, who captured the Australian Open, Indian Wells and Miami titles this year, skipped the entire claycourt season to improve his chances of winning a record eighth title at the All England Club.

title: Davis Cup: Leander Paes brings up ‘doubles fault’
description: After an impressive performance with Saketh Myneni at Davis Cup, Leander Paes lashes out at Rio selection: ‘Sania Mirza and I should’ve been partners’.

title: Davis Cup: Purav Raja replaces injured N Sriram Balaji for Canada tie
description: Purav Raja will now join the team as a reserve, along with fellow reserve Prajnesh Gunneswaran and the nominated quartet of Ramkumar Ramanathan, Yuki Bhambri, Saketh Myneni and Rohan Bopanna.

title: Saketh Myneni, Prajnesh Gunneswaran only Indians left in singles event of KPTI-MSLTA Challenger
description: Saketh Myneni battled through shoulder pain to beat Sidharth Rawat 6-0 2-6 6-1 while Prajnesh pipped Vijay Prashanth 6-4 6-2 in their second round.

title: French Open 2018: Feel like a queen from Wakanda in the new catsuit, says Serena Williams
description: Serena Williams is attempting to win her first Grand Slam Title since her pregnancy at Roland Garros.

title: Nike to continue sponsoring Maria Sharapova despite two-year doping ban
description: Maria Sharapova was punished by a three-member Tennis Anti-Doping Program tribunal appointed by the International Tennis Federation.

title: French Open 2016, Day 8: Wawrinka through to quarters
description: Defending champion Stan Wawrinka moved into the quarter-finals of French Open 2016 in Paris.

title: US Open 2016: Venus Williams crashes out from fourth round
description: Karoline Pliskova reached her first Grand Slam quarterfinal by edging out seven-time major champion Venus Williams 4-6, 6-4, 7-6.

title: ATP Finals: Bryan brothers exit after surprise loss
description: Bob and Mike Bryan bowed out of the tournament after a surprise 6-4 6-4 defeat by alternates Oliver Marach and Mate Pavic on Friday.

title: ‘Why should I give them money?’: Dominic Thiem against Djokovic’s player relief fund
description: The relief fund is aimed to raise around $4.5million to help lower-ranked players when the professional tour is suspended for an indefinite period due to the Covid-19 pandemic.

title: Wimbledon 2018: Stan Wawrinka upsets Grigor Dimitrov
description: Stan Wawrinka, former world number three, whose ranking had dropped to 225 after a knee injury, fought a stubborn and determined match from the baseline to down Grigor Dimitrov.

title: Movement and getting used to slide will be important at French Open, says Yuki Bhambri
description: Yuki Bhambri has had a remarkable year so far by his and Indian tennis' standards. He made inroads into the main draw of the Masters events on the hard courts of Indian Wells and then Miami.

title: Rain looms as Roger Federer, Rafael Nadal start US Open campaign
description: World number one Nadal and Federer, who could meet in the semi-finals, will not be bothered as they are scheduled on the roof-covered centre court against Dusan Lajovic and Frances Tiafoe respectively, with the Swiss closing the night session.

title: Svetlana Kuznetsova opens Sydney defence with win, top seeds withdraw
description: Svetlana Kuznetsova opened the defence of her Sydney International title with a comfortable 6-1 6-4 win over Irina-Camelia Begu.

title: Qualifier Peter Gojowczyk wins maiden title at Moselle Open
description: Qualifier Peter Gojowczyk won his maiden ATP title at the Moselle Open in his first final, defeating seventh-seeded Benoit Paire 7-5, 6-2 Sunday.

title: Wimbledon 2017: Roger Federer’s road to the final
description: Come Sunday and Federer would be walking out to Centre Court at the All England Club vying for his second Grand Slam title of the year. It would be his 29th Grand Slam final and a win would see him lifting the Wimbledon trophy fora record eighth time

title: US Open 2016: Frustrated Andy Murray finds way past pesky Paolo Lorenzi
description: World number two Andy Murray committed 47 errors in the first two sets, including 31 off his forehand, and converted only 4-of-12 break points.

title: Wimbledon 2018: Stan Wawrinka bows out in second round after loss to Thomas Fabbiano
description: Stan Wawrinka's poor run at recent Grand Slams continued when he lost 7-6 6-3 7-6 in the Wimbledon second round against Thomas Fabbiano.

title: Wimbledon 2017: I didn’t expect it to go that easy, says Roger Federer
description: Roger Federer and Andy Murray, much to the delight of the Centre Court crowd, both reached the Wimbledon quarterfinals on Monday. Federer is a seven-time champion at the All England Club and one of the fan favorites. He advanced to the quarterfinals for the 15th time by beating Grigor Dimitrov 6-4, 6-2, 6-4.

title: Sania Mirza goes for ‘gol gappa tasting’ with Roger Federer, Nick Kyrgios
description: Busy playing IPTL in New Delhi, this is what Sania Mirza did alongside Roger Federer and Nick Kyrgios.

title: American teenager Coco Gauff reaches semifinals for first time
description: The 15-year-old Gauff, who reached the fourth round at Wimbledon and third round at the U.S. Open, earned her first win over a top-10 player against the eighth-ranked Bertens.

title: Italian Open win allows Maria Sharapova to qualify for Wimbledon
description: Maria Sharapova will learn on Tuesday if she will be granted a wild card for the French Open this month.

title: How sports industry can protect nature? Dominic Thiem shares his two cents
description: “I think the most important thing is to reduce plastic bottles, to reuse glass bottles, to use huge water dispensers," said Dominic Thiem after being appointed as Rio Open's nature ambassador.

title: Champions Tennis League 2015: I grew up on clay, we learnt to play on that surface, says Thomas Muster
description: For somebody who won 40 out of his 44 titles on clay courts, Thomas Muster rightfully earned the nickname of ‘King of Clay’ in the 1990s.

title: Katerina Siniakova beats top-20 player for sixth time in 2017 in Wuhan Open
description: Katerina Siniakova beat a top-20 player for the sixth time this year when she ousted Kristina Mladenovic of France 6-3, 6-2 in the first round of the Wuhan Open on Sunday.

title: Caroline Wozniacki beats Aryna Sabalenka for 2nd Eastbourne title
description: Wozniacki, who was runner-up last year, triumphed 7-5, 7-6 (5) in just under two hours, sealing the match with a backhand down the line.

title: Injured Simona Halep ’50-50′ for French Open
description: The Romanian posted a composite photograph on her Instagram account showing the 25-year-old having treatment on the injury.

title: Roger Federer, Rafa Nadal win as Team Europe take 7-5 lead in Laver Cup
description: Roger Federer maintained his 100% Laver Cup record against Nick Kyrgios on Saturday with a thrilling 6-7(5) 7-5 10-7 win over the Australian but Team World hit back in the doubles match later on to stay in contention for the title.

title: Daria Kasatkina outlasts Venus Williams to advance to Indian Wells final
description: Daria Kasatkina's win sets up a showdown against either world number one Simona Halep or fellow 20-year-old Naomi Osaka of Japan, who play later on Friday.

title: French Open 2019: Roger Federer beats Casper Ruud, becomes oldest man to reach 4th round since 1972
description: Roger Federer eased past Norway's Casper Ruud 6-3 6-1 7-6(10-8) on Friday to become the oldest male player to reach the fourth round at the French Open in almost 50 years.

title: Maria Sharapova to return in July for World Team Tennis matches
description: Maria Sharapova will return to competitive tennis in July for two World Team Tennis matches. Sharapova recently returned to the WTA Tour after a 15-month doping ban.

title: Toronto film festival to open with ‘Borg/McEnroe’ biopic
description: The premiere of "Borg/McEnroe," which stars Shia LaBeouf as John McEnroe and Sverrir Gudnason as Bjorn Borg, re-enacts the legendary on-court battles between the volatile American and his cucumber-cool Swedish rival.

title: Madrid Open: Novak Djokovic tames Andy Murray, wins record 29th Masters crown
description: Novak Djokovic beats Andy Murray 6-2, 3-6, 6-3 to win Madrid Open for his 29th Masters title, one more than Rafael Nadal.

title: Ramkumar Ramanathan enters semifinals, Leander Paes out of Hall of Fame Open
description: Ramkumar Ramanathan, who had stunned world No. 8 Dominic Thiem at the Antalya Open last year, sent down five aces and converted the three break points that came his way.

title: Serena Williams out of Montreal tourney for personal reasons
description: Serena Williams has pulled out of next week's Rogers Cup hard-court tournament, citing personal reasons.

title: French Open 2017: Meltdown of the year? I was expecting it, says Elina Svitolina
description: Elina Svitolina's spectacular slide in her French Open quarter-final against Simona Halep must be a candidate for meltdown of the year, yet the Ukrainian felt it was not unexpected. Svitolina was serving for the match at 5-1 in the second set but choked and lost 12 of the 13 remaining games.

title: Australian Open Day 4: Medvedev suffers bleeding nose; Nadal, Kyrgios, Thiem, Zverev advance
description: Daniil Medvedev of Russia dealt with spells of resistance from Spanish qualifier Pedro Martinez and a bleeding nose on his way to a 7-5 6-1 6-3 win.

title: US Open champion Sloane Stephens leads US in Fed Cup final against Belarus
description: U.S. Open champion Sloane Stephens will lead the United States against Belarus in the Fed Cup final this month.

title: WTA Finals: Frustrated Naomi Osaka looking for answers after opening defeat
description: Naomi Osaka was left frustrated with her performance after she opened her debut WTA Finals tournament with a 7-5 4-6 6-1 defeat against Sloane Stephens.

title: Stan Wawrinka seals spot in ATP World Tour Finals
description: Stan Wawrinka, Australian Open and French Open winner Novak Djokovic and Wimbledon champion Andy Murray are the first three players that made the cut.

title: US Open: Novak Djokovic dances with fan after easy win
description: Novak Djokovic said he has seen the fan at number of his matches, for a number of years.

title: US Open Preview: Big Three ‘almost impossible’ to beat, dominance to continue
description: Daniil Medvedev, the fifth seed, is widely considered as a possible threat to the hierarchy as he has proven to be the most in-form player in the lead-up to the U.S. Open.

title: Wimbledon 2017: Top players get tough draw, potential Big-4 face-off in men’s semis
description: Andy Murray, bidding for his third title, has been draw in the top-half with Rafael Nadal while seven-time champion Roger Federer has been draw in the bottom half of the men's singles alongwith three-time champion Novak Djokovic.

title: Roger Federer wins BBC Sports Personality Award for fourth time
description: Roger Federer won the BBC Overseas Sports Personality of the Year award for a record fourth time following a year in which he won two Grand Slam titles.

title: AITA names Leander Paes in Davis Cup squad, asks players to ‘put differences aside’
description: India’s highest ranked singles player Yuki Bhambri (110) leads the lineup followed by the second and third ranked Ramkumar Ramanathan (135) and Sumit Nagal (223).

title: Wimbledon 2017: Andy Murray, Rafa Nadal, Azarenka, Halep advance to Round 4
description: Wimbledon 2017 Day 5 saw the top seeds move into the next round in both the men's and women's singles category. Rafael Nadal, Andy Murray, Victoria Azarenka, Simona Halep and Jo Konta all posted wins in their respective matches.

title: India’s Davis Cup tie against Pakistan postponed to November
description: The decision comes just a week after the ITF rejected the All India Tennis Associations’ (AITA) proposal for the tie to either be shifted to a neutral venue or played at a later date.

title: ATP Finals: Roger Federer opens seventh title bid with victory over Jack Sock
description: Roger Federer began his bid for a record-stretching seventh ATP Finals crown with a 6-4 7-6(4) win over Jack Sock.

title: Bethanie Mattek-Sands and Lucie Safarova win French Open doubles, third straight major
description: Bethanie Mattek-Sands, however, praised her opponents, who had dropped just one set on their way to the final. "You guys have done a great job and you're an awesome team,” the 32-year-old said. "I’m sure we're gonna be facing you again soon."

title: Rafael Nadal shines in comfortable victory over David Ferrer in Barcelona
description: Rafael Nadal promptly saw out the set when play resumed and broke Ferrer in the first game of the second but then lost a service game, which made it 2-2.

title: Milos Raonic knocks out Rafael Nadal to join Stan Wawrinka in Brisbane semis
description: Milos Raonic blasted 50 winners, including 23 aces, to overcome the Spaniard 4-6 6-3 6-4 and set up a last-four clash with Grigor Dimitrov.

title: French Open organisers working with authorities to avoid US Open clash
description: The French Open had originally been due to start on Sunday, but the coronavirus crisis forced organisers to postpone the start to September 20, one week after the scheduled final of the US Open.

title: Former Wimbledon finalist Agnieszka Radwanska retires from tennis
description: Agnieszka Radwanska won 20 WTA titles in her career. She reached the Wimbledon final in 2012, losing to Serena Williams in three sets.

title: WTA boss keen to let coaches instruct players from stands
description: Under the existing rules, players are allowed to take on-court coaching timeouts during WTA events.

title: Angelique Kerber beats Karolina Pliskova 6-3, 4-6, 6-4 to lift US Open title: As it happened
description: Angelique Kerber picked up her second Grand Slam trophy of the year by lifting the US Open title at Flushing Meadows.

title: Sumit Nagal to make Grand Slam debut against peerless Roger Federer
description: From hanging around the outer courts in Pune, Nagal has secured himself a spot in the main draw of a Grand Slam for the first time in his career, and will play his first-round match in the largest tennis arena in the world, Arthur Ashe Stadium against Federer.

title: Sania Mirza-Martina Hingis seal WTA Year-End No.1 ranking
description: Sania Mirza-Martina Hingis had as many as eight titiles this year which speaks volumes of their success in 2015.

title: Ankita Raina wins first singles title of 2019 season in Singapore
description: Ankita Raina toppled four seeded players in the tournament starting with Dutch eighth seed Lesley Kerkhove in the second round.

title: With COVID-19 at large, professional tennis events face an existential threat
description: With professional tennis on hold until at least June, the sport’s administrators and players are scrambling to cut their losses as tournaments are postponed or cancelled en masse.

title: US Open 2017: Five things to watch out for on Day 2
description: Roger Federer's first appearance is likely to attract a variety of celebrities, who will walk the tournament's famed Blue Carpet on their way into the USTA Billie Jean King National Tennis Center.

title: French Open 2019: Rafael Nadal defeats Roger Federer in straight sets to storm into finals
description: Rafael Nadal defeated Roger Federer 6-3 6-4 6-2 to storm into his 12th final at Roland Garros.

title: French Open: Roger Federer left fuming despite an easy win
description: Federer was in full control against Alejandro Falla and completed a 6-3 6-3 6-4 win in 1st round.

title: Gender violence doesn’t lie in extremities but happens everywhere, says Sania Mirza
description: Sharing her journey and her parents support, Sania Mirza said that she was never told by her parents that she might not be able to do something because she is a girl and that she won't be able to follow her dreams.

title: Wu Yibing gives China its first boys’ grand slam title at US Open
description: Wu Yibing capped a highly successful week in New York by beating Argentine top seed Axel Geller 6-4, 6-4 to add the junior singles title to the boys' doubles crown he won with Taiwan's Hsu Yu-hsiou on Saturday.

title: Rafael Nadal withdraws, Andy Murray loses to Daniel Medvedev in Brisbane
description: World number two Rafael Nadal endured an injury-plagued 2018 season that saw him contest only nine tournaments due to hip, knee, abdomen and ankle injuries.

title: Roger Federer back into the top 10 with Australian Open win
description: Roger Federer won his 18th Grand Slam title by beating Rafael Nadal 6-4, 3-6, 6-1,3-6, 6-3.

title: Simona Halep pulls out of Birmingham event with ankle injury
description: Halep, the beaten finalist in the French Open last week, is the latest top player to pull out from the event after Czech world number three Karolina Pliskova opted to rest her injured elbow ahead of Wimbledon.

title: Rafael Nadal beats Novak Djokovic 6-2, 6-4, books place in Madrid Open final
description: Rafael Nadal broke his seven-game losing streak against Novak Djokovic to book a place in the Madrid Open final.

title: Novak Djokovic and wife test negative for coronavirus
description: Novak Djokovic had tested positive for the virus 10 days ago after playing in an exhibition series he organized in Serbia and Croatia with zero social distancing amid the pandemic.

title: Dominika Cibulkova beats Elise Mertens to reach Connecticut Open final
description: Dominika Cibulkova is looking for her first title of the season in the final tune-up before the U.S. Open, which begins from Monday. She will face the winner of the semifinal between top-seeded defending champion Agnieszka Radwanska and Daria Gavilova.

title: Stefanos Tsitsipas wins Stockholm Open, first Greek to claim ATP title
description: Stefanos Tsitsipas became the first Greek tennis player to win an ATP World Tour title when he beat Ernests Gulbis 6-4, 6-4 in the final of the Stockholm Open on Sunday.

title: Ilie Nastase apologises for racist comments on Serena Williams
description: Ilie Nastase apologised for racist comments about Serena Williams and fabusive Fed Cup tirade that saw him suspended by ITF.

description: Sania Mirza-Martina Hingis claim their first Wimbledon doubles title together on Saturday.

title: US Open 2019: From Serena Williams to the Big 3, here is all you need to know
description: Djokovic, Nadal, and Federer have combined to take 11 Slam titles in a row and 54 of the past 65. One thing to keep an eye on: Federer and Nadal have played each other 40 times but never at the U.S. Open. It could only happen if both reach the Sept. 8 final.

title: French Open 2017: All too easy for Rafael Nadal
description: Rafael Nadal moved into the third round of French Open 2017 after a comfortable 6-1 6-4 6-3 win over Robin Haase of Netherlands. The Spaniard is looking for a record tenth title in Paris and missing out on two consecutive occasions in 2015 and 2016.

title: Wimbledon prize money rise by 11.8 percent
description: Wimbledon prize money will total 38 million pounds ($49 million) for this year's championships, a rise of 11.8 percent, the All England Club announced on Tuesday.

title: In pursuit of second Wimbledon crown, Andy Murray named third seed

title: After Wimbledon win, I have more pressure and responsibility, acknowledges Garbine Muguruza
description: In 2016, following her success against Serena Williams at the French Open, Garbine Muguruza went out in the second round of Wimbledon losing to Jana Cepelova. She later experienced early exits at the Rio Olympics and then at US Open.

description: Garbine Muguruza defeated Simona Halep 6-1, 6-0 for her first Western & Southern Open title on Sunday. On the men's side, seventh-seeded Grigor Dimitrov beat Nick Kyrgios 6-3, 7-5 for his first ATP Masters title.

title: Australian Open 2018: Novak Djokovic survives Melbourne furnace to beat Gael Monfils
description: Novak Djokovic survived the Rod Laver Arena furnace to reach the third round of the Australian Open with a 4-6 6-3 6-1 6-3 victory over Gael Monfils on Thursday.

description: The Indo-Chinese pair of Pranjala Yadlapalli and Xiaoxi Zhao, however, denied Rutuja a double crown by winning the women's doubles title. In a well-contested singles final, Rutuja and Mahak traded service breaks thrice before the senior player got a decisive break in the 9th game and held her serve in the next.

title: Great Britain, Argentina receive 2019 Davis Cup finals wild card
description: Great Britain and Argentina's seeded place in the qualifiers will go to Australia and Switzerland who went out from the 2018 world group as the next best ranked teams.

title: In Japan, fans never give up on their star Kei Nishikori

title: Andy Murray to miss Britain’s Davis Cup tie against France

description: Rohan Bopanna and his Romanian partner Florin Mergea had earned 360 points with a semifinal place at Rome Masters

title: French Open 2016: Proud I have managed to reach finals of all four Grand Slams, says Andy Murray
description: Andy Murray went into full throttle mode to subdue holder Stan Wawrinka in Friday's semi-final.

description: Rafa Nadal suffered a shock 6-4 6-2 semi-final defeat against flamboyant Italian Fabio Fognini at the Monte Carlo Masters on Saturday, showing rare signs of weakness five weeks before the French Open.

title: Federer begins hardcourt campaign in style

title: French Open 2020 Women’s Final, Iga Swiatek vs Sofia Kenin Live Streaming: When and where to watch
description: French Open 2020 Women's Final, Iga Swiatek vs Sofia Kenin Tennis Live Score Streaming: Iga Swiatek vs Sofia Kenin in French Open Women's singles final

title: Roger Federer says he will probably rest until French Open

title: Davis Cup: Novak Djokovic ties Serbia 2-2 against Kazakhstan

title: Prone to cramps but Saketh Myneni insists no fitness issues

title: Prajnesh hopes to bounce back on home soil

description: Rafa Nadal paid tribute to his uncle and coach Toni after winning a record-extending 10th French Open title. Toni Nadal is planning to step down as his nephew's head coach at the end of the season.

title: I’ve always wanted to play with Rafa Nadal, says Roger Federer
description: Roger Federer, the world number nine, is due to figure with sixth-ranked Rafa Nadal at the Laver Cup.

title: Telengana government felicitates Sania Mirza with Rs one crore for US Open win
description: Sania was given Rs 1 crore prior to the US Open and another Rs 1 crore was handed over to her on Thursday.

title: French Open 2018: Dominic Thiem beats Marco Cecchinato, reaches first Grand Slam final
description: Dominic Thiem reached the first Grand Slam final of his career by ending the surprising run of 72nd-ranked Marco Cecchinato of Italy at Roland Garros.

title: Colin Kaepernick thanks first NFL players to kneel during national anthem
description: Colin Kaepernick used social media to thank the first two players who knelt during the playing of the United States national anthem on the opening Sunday of the National Football League season.

title: ‘Organising US Open is impossible, the rules are extreme’: Novak Djokovic
description: Novak Djokovic believes the rules that players will have to follow for US Open this year are quite rigorous, starting from having to sleep at the airport to bringing just one person to the club.

title: French Open is going to be our toughest Grand Slam to win: Sania Mirza
description: Having won three Grand Slam titles in a row, Sania Mirza and Martina would hope to maintain the winning streak at the French Open.

title: IPTL: Indian Aces lose 20-27 to Japan Warriors
description: In the other match of the day, Singapore Slammers beat UAE Royals 30-18.

title: Davis Cup: Argentina advances to 11th semis in 14 years
description: Federico Delbonis beat Fabio Fognini 6-4, 7-5, 3-6, 7-5 in an entertaining 3 1/2 hours for the Argentines to win their quarterfinal 3-1.

title: Another first for Nishikori adds to his torchbearer status
description: Japan’s Kei Nishikori is the first Asian to make it into the elite eightman season finale.

title: Serena Williams ousts Simona Halep to set up Agnieska Radwanska semi at Indian Wells
description: A right knee injury forced Serena Williams to withdraw from the event last year, when she ended a self-imposed 14-year absence at the tournament.

title: Alexander Zverev beats Alex de Minaur for second consecutive Citi Open title
description: Alexander Zverev became the first man in nearly a decade to win consecutive titles at Washington's hard-court tuneup for the US Open.

title: Bangalore first choice venue for India-Uzbekistan Davis Cup tie
description: Bangalore is the front runner to host the India vs Uzbekistan Davis Cup tie that starts on April 7.

title: Australian Open 2019: Prajnesh Gunneswaran win away from main draw; Raina, Ramkumar exit
description: Injured Yuki Bhambri had played in all four Grand Slam main draws in 2018. Placed 132 in the world rankings, Ramkumar played a very close match before losing 7-5 5-7 6-7(6) to Germany's Rudolf Molleker, ranked 207.

title: Novak Djokovic ‘happy’ to play US Open 2020 despite coronavirus fears
description: Novak Djokovic said that it was not an easy decision to make.

title: Rohan Bopanna-Florin Mergea win Mercedes Cup men’s doubles title
description: Bopanna-Mergea eked out a 5-7 6-2 10-7 win over third seeded Peya-Soares in one hour and 11 minutes.

title: French Open 2017: Grigor Dimitrov rapier fails to pierce Pablo Carreno Busta
description: In a contest between two closely matched gladiators, Grigor Dimitrov came up against the bludgeon of Spain's Pablo Carreno Busta. The Bulgarian, who has a stylish all-round game, which was to prove his downfall in a 7-5 6-3 6-4 defeat.

title: Sam Querrey hails American success at Wimbledon 2016
description: The U.S. had six players in the singles fourth round, the country's highest number since 2004.

title: Bad day for No 1s: Novak Djokovic, Naomi Osaka upset at Indian Wells
description: It was a tough day for seeded players at the BNP Paribas Open on Tuesday, with Novak Djokovic and Naomi Osaka, the world's top-ranked players, ushered out in the desert.

title: Happy birthday Roger Federer: Sachin Tendulkar wishes ‘champ’ Roger Federer on 37th birthday
description: Former India skipper Sachin Tendulkar wished Roger Federer on his 37th birthday as he posted a picture with the tennis star on his official Twitter handle

title: Murray-Williams dream team is on as Serena says yes
description: Andy Murray wanted it, the British fans were desperate for it and the media were working themselves into a frenzy about it and on Tuesday it was confirmed that Serena Williams had said yes.

title: Rafael Nada beats David Goffin to set up Monte Carlo Masters final against Albert Ramos-Vinolas
description: Rafael Nadal beat David Goffin 6-3 6-1 to move to the Monte Carlo Masters and one step closer to 10th title in Monaco.

title: Greek tennis player handed lifetime ban for corruption
description: Konstantinos Mikos was banned for life after being found guilty of four corruption offenses.

title: Mommy to be Sania Mirza back home in Hyderabad after Dubai trip
description: Sania Mirza announced in April and she and husband Shoaib Malik were expecting a child. Her due date is in October.

title: Rafael Nadal returns for Spain’s David Cup playoff against Denmark
description: Rafa Nadal will return to Spain's Davis Cup team for the first time in two years.

title: Australia Open 2018: Roger Federer bests Richard Gasquet, enters fourth round in Melbourne
description: Roger Federer beat Frenchman Richard Gasquet 6-2 7-5 6-4 to advance to the fourth round of Australian Open.

title: If he deserves, he’ll be in the Davis Cup team: AITA on Leander Paes
description: This comes just a month after the AITA urged Leander Paes to retire to make way for the younger and higher ranked doubles players.

title: Tennis: Novak Djokovic cruises into second round in Japan Open, Naomi Osaka eases into China Open last 16
description: Playing in his first singles match since retiring from his U.S. Open fourth-round match with Stan Wawrinka due to a left shoulder issue, the Serb showed he was fighting fit as he fired seven aces and won 84% of points on his first serve.

title: Whatever I have left in me, I will put it out on court: Novak Djokovic
description: Djokovic might have to do a lot of scurrying for the ball against Wawrinka, which can cause him trouble.

title: US Open: Serena Williams ‘out of line’ but both sides share blame, says Billie Jean King
description: Serena Williams was issued a warning, point and then game penalty after she argued with Ramos during the final, which was won 6-2 6-4 by Japan's Naomi Osaka.

title: Rafael Nadal returns to World No 1 with Rome title
description: Rafael Nadal returned to World No 1 ranking a week after losing the spot to Roger Federer with defeat in Madrid over Dominic Thiem.

title: Lucie Safarova slams Czech friends over poor sportsmanship at US Open 2017
description: Lucie Safarova lashed out at her fellow Czech Republic players Lucie Hradecka and Katerina Siniakova for poor sportsmanship during her semifinal loss at the US Open while partnering another Czech Barbora Strycova.

title: Roger Federer-Stan Wawrinka win in style, give Switzerland 2-1 lead
description: Federer-Wawrinka won 6-3, 7-5, 6-4 to give Switzerland a 2-1 lead over France in Davis Cup final.

title: Fed Cup: Ankita Raina shows mettle against higher-ranked Yulia Putintseva
description: While India lost the Fed Cup Asia/Oceania Group I tie 1-2, Ankita Raina showed why she has long been the top women's singles player in the country.

title: Sania Mirza-Martina Hingis win Brisbane International doubles title
description: Sania Mirza and Martina Hingis registered their 26th win in a row and lifted their first title of 2016.

title: Roger Federer out of French Open due to knee injury
description: World no 3 Roger Federer won't participate in the upcoming edition of French Open due to a knee injury.

title: No guarantee of Australian Open wildcard for Bernard Tomic
description: Tomic has raised fears about his mental state, describing himself as "bored" with tennis and feeling "trapped" in the game during media interviews.

title: Roger Federer overtakes Serena Williams with most Grand Slam matches won
description: Roger Federer on Saturday got the better of 27th seed Mischa Zverev, defeating him 7-6 (3), 6-4, 6-4 in one hour and 50 minutes to register his 87th Wimbledon win. He overtook Serena Williams for the most match wins in Grand Slam.

title: Sania Mirza-Cara Black storm into Tokyo Open semi-final
description: Sania and Cara dispatched the Swiss pair 6-4 6-2 in the quarterfinals of the USD 1,000,000 hard court event.

title: Borna Coric downs second-seeded Albert Ramos-Vinolas to reach semi-finals in Morocco
description: Borna Coric, advancing to his first ATP semifinal since this clay event last year, broke Ramos-Vinolas three times to prevail in 2 1/2 hours.

title: Leander Paes becomes most successful doubles player in Davis Cup
description: Leander Paes became the most successful doubles player in the history of Davis Cup as he combined with Rohan Bopanna to grab a record 43rd win.

title: Roger Federer receives twin nominations for 2018 Laureus World Sports Awards
description: Regarded as the Oscar of sports, the nominations for 2018 Laureus World Sports Awards were finalised following a ballot by the world's sports media.

title: Jelena Ostapenko ousts Johanna Konta in Rome to set up Maria Sharapova clash
description: Jelena Ostapenko ruined Johanna Konta's birthday celebrations at the Italian Open on Sunday by coming from a set down to beat the Briton 2-6 6-3 6-4.

title: Novak Djokovic could face Roger Federer in Wimbledon semifinals
description: Roger Federer has been placed in defending champion Novak Djokovic's top half of the Wimbledon draw.

title: British tennis body to vote against controversial Davis Cup reform
description: The LTA said on Wednesday that while they remain supportive of the ITF, it is "unable to support their proposed Davis Cup reforms at this time."

title: Ramkumar Ramanathan standing on cusp of ATP top-100 ranking following Newport loss
description: At the Newport ATP 250 event in Rhode Island, Ramkumar came up against world no 48 Steve Johnson, and eventually lost 5-7, 6-3, 2-6 to the American.

title: Novak Djokovic: Records, facts, Grand Slam titles, career stats
description: Novak Djokovic became the first player since Rod Laver in 1969 to hold all four Grand Slam titles at the same time.
